firstComment: Technological advances, particularly in automation, artificial intelligence, and decentralized systems like blockchain, are poised to disrupt traditional economic structures, potentially leading to the needless distribution of money or currency. Automation and AI are reducing the need for human labor in many industries, which could result in widespread job displacement and economic inequality, prompting governments and organizations to implement measures like universal basic income (UBI) to redistribute wealth. Blockchain and cryptocurrencies enable peer-to-peer transactions without intermediaries, which could render traditional banking systems less relevant and lead to unregulated or speculative currency flows. Additionally, advancements in digital payment systems and central bank digital currencies (CBDCs) may streamline transactions but could also enable excessive or poorly targeted stimulus distributions, as seen in some pandemic-era relief programs. While these technologies aim to enhance efficiency and access, they risk creating scenarios where currency is distributed without sufficient economic grounding, potentially fueling inflation, speculative bubbles, or misaligned incentives if not carefully managed.

Visualising entire chatgpt conversation here’s how:

What if you could see your thoughts as a neural map?

Imagine visualizing your entire ChatGPT conversation history as a 3D web of interconnected ideas.

Here’s how that could be done:

- Export the chat history from ChatGPT settings
- Clean the messages to isolate the raw conversations
- Generate embeddings using an AI model like text-embedding-3-small
- Measure similarity between conversations using cosine distance
- Build a graph with similar thoughts linked
- Visualize it in 3D using tools like Gephi, Graphistry, or 3d-force-graph.js

The result:

A living, breathing map of one’s thought patterns — clustered by topics, connected by curiosity, and layered with personal evolution.

The next frontier might not be AI doing the thinking for us…

…but showing us how we think.

Thoughts on this?

caption:
For the longest time, I thought I was doing everything right.
→ Posting consistently
→ Sharing value
→ Creating “good content”

But my audience?
Flatlined.
Engagement? Mid.
Sales? Inconsistent.

I thought maybe I wasn’t trying hard enough.
But what I’ve learned since changed everything:

It’s not about working harder.
It’s about being clearer.

Here’s what I had to unlearn:

1️⃣ People weren’t ignoring me.
They were confused.
→ What exactly do I do?
→ Who is it for?
→ Why should they care?

Even when the content looked good — if the message wasn’t sharp, it didn’t connect.

2️⃣ I was teaching, not leading.
I gave tips. I gave value.
But I wasn’t giving perspective.
→ No personal edge.
→ No emotional tension.
→ No positioning.

I sounded helpful — but not bookable.

3️⃣ I was saying too much… and still saying nothing.
The feed was full with content. But the message was blurry.
I had to stop posting from pressure — and start posting with precision.

If you’re showing up and still feeling invisible…
It’s not because you’re not good enough.
It’s because your clarity isn’t cutting through yet.

When it does?
The brand, the audience, the sales — it all changes.

DM “BRAND” if you want help fixing your message and finally make your content land.

The chaos behind “multiple income streams” that nobody talks about...

Today I juggled a retainer call, filmed content for a roofing client, hopped on sales calls, edited videos, and somehow squeezed in writing UGC proposals. 5 different ways I made money today. And my brain is FRIED.
Everyone makes this stuff sound so easy - like you just post content and money appears. But nobody tells you about taking a client call while your editing software crashes, or writing proposals in your car between meetings.
Some days I question if I’m actually building a business or just doing 10 jobs poorly 😅

But then I remember why I started this. Last month when my biggest client paused their contract, I didn’t panic. The UGC work covered rent. The retainer calls kept coming. The editing gigs filled the gaps.
That’s the real power of multiple streams - it’s not about getting rich quick. It’s about never having to put all your eggs in one basket again.

If you’re building multiple streams too, just know - the juggling act is normal. The overwhelm is temporary. But the security? That’s worth fighting for.

If you’re an entrepreneur, you need to memorize this response:

“That’s an amazing idea. It’s not a priority right now. But I will add it to our big ideas list. Thank you for sharing it.”

Businesses rarely die from a lack of good ideas. They die from a lack of good execution.

After 20+ years as a singer, songwriter and producer, I walked away from my dream job - devastated. I was broke, exhausted, and honestly heartbroken that something I loved so much didn’t love me back like I needed it to. I thought my days of creating for a living were over. 

Little did I realize the skills I learned as an artist would transfer to new dreams - first my own creative agency, then co-founding a health food restaurant and meal prep company (with 2 storefronts, an incredible team of over 25 staff, millions in sales and thousands of customers). 

Seven years later and I’m actually grateful I walked away from my dream job when I did. It helped me fall in love with music again, and it taught me that I had so many other dreams and ideas just waiting to be unlocked. 

For everything there is a season - even for your dreams. Don’t be afraid to reinvent yourself. 

#motivation #entrepreneur #musician #businessowner #businesstips #musicianlife #story #failure

Self-love is a journey that can be difficult to navigate. One of the biggest obstacles that many of us face is the pressure to be perfect. We are bombarded with images of “perfect” bodies, “perfect” lives, and “perfect” relationships. It’s easy to get caught up in this idea that we have to be perfect in order to be worthy of love and acceptance. 

But the truth is, perfection is a myth. We are all flawed, and that’s okay. 

In fact, it’s more than okay. Our flaws are what make us unique and interesting. They are the imperfections that make us human. Embracing our flaws and loving ourselves, despite them, is what truly allows us to be confident and authentic. 1️⃣ Your “best” content won’t always perform.

The post you spent 4 hours editing might flop. The one you made in 30 seconds while half-asleep might go viral. The algorithm does not care about your effort.

2️⃣ “Just be consistent” is the worst advice

Consistency without clarity = burnout. Know why you’re showing up, not just how often.

3️⃣ Strangers will be your biggest supporters. 

Having an audience means being seen, but not everyone will clap. 

4️⃣ Growth doesn’t always mean money.

Most creators have no business strategy which is why so many struggled to monetise. Don’t ever rely on brand deals or post and hope for the best.

Comment “EDIT” and I’ll send a video tutorial on the technique used in this video: the Match Cut.

More context 👇

This video uses just one technique:
🔥✂️ The Match Cut

🎥 Filming

Take a bunch of pictures of the same subject. 

Make sure you have guidelines turned on in your camera.

Make sure you keep the following the same between each shot
1️⃣ Focal length
2️⃣ Distance to camera
3️⃣ Position within camera

💻 Editing

1️⃣ Choose one shot as the reference shot.
2️⃣ For each of the other shots, set the opacity to 50% so you can line it up perfectly.
3️⃣ Add click sounds to help sell the effect

Here’s what you should NOT do if you want to get VC funding. Founder PSA

Tutorial 👇

🎥 Filming

Record 3 different shots using a tripod:
1️⃣ [REAL] throw the hat
2️⃣ [PRETEND] throw the hat - same position as 1st shot but w/o the hat
3️⃣ close up of the hat spinning - attach it to a string so that it spins naturally

💻 Editing
1️⃣ mask out the hat from the close up clip
2️⃣ start with the REAL clip. right after the hat leaves your hand, cut to the PRETEND clip
3️⃣ add the masked out hat. use keyframes to make it start small at first. then come right in front of the camera and then get small again as it hits you in the head.
4️⃣ apply speed ramping

essential things to know about equity if you’re working at a startup that could quite literally save you a ton of money one day

(none of this is financial advice, please do your own research)

Compare two startup equity paths ⬇️

Scenario 1: Status quo
- You get 100K options
- Strike price: $0.10/share
- You don’t early exercise
- Company grows → $10/share
- Taxable income at exercise:
$9.90 × 100K = $990K
- You owe ~37% income tax = $366K
- You net: ~$624K

Scenario 2: Early exercise
- Same 100K options @ $0.10/share
- You early exercise → pay $10K now
- FMV = strike → no tax owed now
- Company grows → $10/share
- You owe long-term cap gains (15–20%)
- Tax = ~$150K, you net ~$840K

⚠️ Notes:
- Not financial advice — this stuff is nuanced
- You must file an 83(b) if early exercising
- There’s risk: if startup fails, you lose your $10K

(not me filming a very serious video while I’m in line at CVS 🫠💀)

Here’s how I did it 👇🏽
👑 Share this with someone who’s tryna grow

I went from:
✅ 0 to 25K followers in ~100 days

with ZERO editing or content creation experience.

It came down to these 4 things:

1️⃣ Stop chasing “original” 
- It’s almost impossible to always be original and win consistently, it leads to burnout every time.
Instead:
- Study creators in your niche.
- Find videos that did 5-10x better than their usual content.
-  Reverse engineer: What hooked you? What could’ve been better? What’s your unique spin?
- Then make it yours. Tweak the idea. Build on it, and improve the parts you felt were off. DONT STEAL.

That being said, if you come up with an original idea that you think has potential, definitely go for it!

2️⃣ Storytelling changed everything
- The moment I learned basic storytelling, minor tweaks to my scripts led to MASSIVE results.

- People don’t just want information - they want to feel something. If you can make your viewer curious and emotionally invested while getting your point across, you win.

3️⃣ Play the long game
- Full honesty: I know I could hit 100K+ if I just spammed pure storytelling content.

- But virality ≠ money. I’m still figuring out how to make my educational videos perform as well as storytelling ones because educational content attracts “ideal buyers” for future monetization. If you’re thinking about monetizing down the line, make sure you’re bringing in the right audience, not just chasing viral hits.

4️⃣ Consistency beats perfection

- 80% of your followers will come from 10-20% of your videos. 

- That’s reality for 99.9% of creators. Not every video will bang - I used to put so much mental pressure on myself to always “get it right.” Just focus on showing up and improving one thing each video.

🎁 Comment “STORY” and I’ll send you the storytelling guide that completely transformed my content

KEEP GOING, because most people won’t.

My Founder Moment

I got into content bc I want to create something bigger than myself. To build a platform and start a movement.

And I won’t be able to do through just brand deals and IG reels.

The same way I had to experiment and fail to build my personal brand, I need to experiment and fail to build my business.

But I’ve been holding myself back.

I’ve been so afraid of being labeled as a sellout that I’ve been overthinking and procrastinating and not taking action.

So this is me ripping off the bandaid.

This is me announcing to the world that I will be launching my own products and services.

caption:
Ep. 4 How much it costs to ATTEND a wedding (as a guest and a bridesmaid)

I actually don’t say yes to all the weddings I’m invited to. I also did not choose bridesmaids until really late because I was too afraid of putting that kind of pressure on anyone. 😳 Attending weddings have very real costs!

I’m genuinely surprised by how high our turnout rate was. For the friends who couldn’t make it, we were absolutely not offended whatsoever. Asking people to take time off, fly internationally, and spend all that money is a lot! 

Have you declined a wedding invite before due to costs or other sticky reasons? 

Have you declined being a bridesmaid or groomsman before? 👀🍵

PS. This concludes our wedding finances deep talks for now. The next wave of posts will be the actual wedding. We will have more wedding finances debriefs after though. Stay tuned!

caption:
Here’s how I did it 👇🏽
👑 Share this with someone who’s tryna grow

I went from:
✅ 0 to 25K followers in ~100 days

with ZERO editing or content creation experience.

It came down to these 4 things:

1️⃣ Stop chasing “original” 
- It’s almost impossible to always be original and win consistently, it leads to burnout every time.
Instead:
- Study creators in your niche.
- Find videos that did 5-10x better than their usual content.
-  Reverse engineer: What hooked you? What could’ve been better? What’s your unique spin?
- Then make it yours. Tweak the idea. Build on it, and improve the parts you felt were off. DONT STEAL.

That being said, if you come up with an original idea that you think has potential, definitely go for it!

2️⃣ Storytelling changed everything
- The moment I learned basic storytelling, minor tweaks to my scripts led to MASSIVE results.

- People don’t just want information - they want to feel something. If you can make your viewer curious and emotionally invested while getting your point across, you win.

3️⃣ Play the long game
- Full honesty: I know I could hit 100K+ if I just spammed pure storytelling content.

- But virality ≠ money. I’m still figuring out how to make my educational videos perform as well as storytelling ones because educational content attracts “ideal buyers” for future monetization. If you’re thinking about monetizing down the line, make sure you’re bringing in the right audience, not just chasing viral hits.

4️⃣ Consistency beats perfection

- 80% of your followers will come from 10-20% of your videos. 

- That’s reality for 99.9% of creators. Not every video will bang - I used to put so much mental pressure on myself to always “get it right.” Just focus on showing up and improving one thing each video.

🎁 Comment “STORY” and I’ll send you the storytelling guide that completely transformed my content

KEEP GOING, because most people won’t.

caption:
I remember when turning 26 scared me because it sounded old and I figured my life would be dialled by 25. Suddenly, there I was at 26 - didn’t own a house yet (had just moved back in with my parents), wasn’t in a serious relationship (thought I’d have a family by then), and had yet to reach some of the milestones I had set for my career. 

It caused nearly crippling anxiety where I didn’t even want to get out of bed for a while. 

Now at 40, I am more sure than ever that my best years are ahead of me. The thing that changed? My mind. I just decided one day that I refuse to be someone who lives a less exciting life as I get older. I’m ok with my plans being “pencilled in” because sometimes God’s plan is different and actually better than the one I could have imagined. And I refuse to “let myself go” just because that’s what often happens when people get older. 

I’m stronger and in better shape now than I’ve ever been. Sharper and much more experienced in business. And social skills? Way less awkward moments. 😮‍💨😂 I know who I am and I’m comfortable in my own skin.

Society tells you to enjoy your teens and 20’s while you’ve got them, but I think your 30’s, 40’s, 50’s+ are only limited by one thing - you and the story you tell yourself. 🖤👊🏼 

#mindsetmotivation #aging #entrepreneurship #businesstiktok #mensmentalhealthmonth #mensmentalhealth

It’s functional - machine washable (which is really helpful with a dog), but still feels like a quality, elevated rug.

caption:
In Taiwanese culture, the bride actually wears 3 dresses at the wedding banquet and does a grand entrance in each of them 😳😳 usually it’s 1 white wedding dress, then 1 colored dress, and then 1 dress to send the guests out “送客”

I was like “wait a min - doesn’t that mean I only get to wear each dress for like 30 min each?” It takes about 30 min to change into a new dress and look btw 🫠

So I decided to work with @sofashiba who’s a commercial videographer in Taipei. We ran around the city’s most iconic spots in these big ass dresses on the streets to get these shots on the morning of the banquet 😮‍💨 I’ll likely never wear dresses this pretty again, so I really wanted to remember them!! (YouTube vlog of the banquet day coming out Sunday🤞!!) 

You’ve already seen the pink dress in the musical performance - that’s the one where the bottom half can be removed! (Also wuddaheck- how did that video go so viral?? 3M views in a day??! INSANE) 

The white dress is gorgeous, but I think looks much better indoors. 

The red dress is my absolute favorite. The shape and color is electric!! 

I rented these dresses at @linli_boutique !!! If you ever need to glam up in Taipei, they’re your people!

caption:
1️⃣ Your “best” content won’t always perform.

The post you spent 4 hours editing might flop. The one you made in 30 seconds while half-asleep might go viral. The algorithm does not care about your effort.

2️⃣ “Just be consistent” is the worst advice

Consistency without clarity = burnout. Know why you’re showing up, not just how often.

3️⃣ Strangers will be your biggest supporters. 

Having an audience means being seen, but not everyone will clap. 

4️⃣ Growth doesn’t always mean money.

Most creators have no business strategy which is why so many struggled to monetise. Don’t ever rely on brand deals or post and hope for the best.

This mistake cost us 10 lakhs and 2 months to fix!

It’s very easy to fall into the feature trap early on thinking that more features = better product and better competitive advantage in the market. 

Secondly, we benchmarked too much on what works in the US market thinking that something that works there will work here too. 

But we were wrong about both. 

First product failed, we ended up spending an extra 10 lakhs to reformulate and went behind by 2 months! 

10 lakhs may not sound much but trust me for a young startup like ours we need to think for every 10k we spend. 

Biggest learning : Always start with the customer. Understand their needs deeply and solve their problems. 

When we did just that both our revenues and repeat rates went up 

#startup #founder #vlog #tip #health #entrepreneur #entrepreneurship #journey

If you’re an aspiring founder, pay attention to Storytelling. It’s highly underrated 

But trust me, this is one thing I put to use all the time - be it pitch meetings, content, or even brand positioning work. 

It’s both art and science and takes practice to get better at (I am still learning too) but once become good at it, it gives you an unfair advantage. 

My top books to learn more are 

1. Storyworthy by Matthew Dicks
2. Contagious by Jonah Berger
3. Building a story brand by Donald Miller

- in the heart of Sydney’s twinkling cityscape, Jai and Afsana embarked on an evening that neither would forget. As the setting sun painted the horizon with hues of pink and purple, the two stepped out, elegantly attired. Afsana wore a graceful black dress that flowed like the dark, tranquil waters of the Harbour. Jai, in contrast, wore a sharp black tuxedo, echoing the silhouette of Sydney’s architectural marvels.

The evening began with a candlelit dinner at a rooftop restaurant overlooking the Sydney Opera House. The mellow light from the candles reflected in Afsana’s eyes, revealing a depth that pulled Jai in, much like the vast Australian night sky pulls one into its myriad constellations. Their conversation flowed effortlessly, much like the waters beneath the Harbour Bridge, punctuated with laughter and shared dreams.

As dinner concluded, they took a leisurely walk along the Circular Quay. The cool breeze from the ocean intertwined with the melodies of street musicians, setting a romantic ambiance. With every step, the dazzling lights of the city seemed to fade into the background, replaced by a world only they could perceive.

With the Sydney Tower Eye witnessing their journey from afar, they spoke of dreams, fears, and everything in between. As they walked and talked, it felt as if the universe had slowed its pace just for them, allowing them a moment in eternity.

Under the canopy of the starlit sky, by the shores of the Pacific, they paused. Afsana looked deep into Jai’s eyes and whispered, “Tonight, amidst this vast universe of flesh and concrete, it feels like we’re just two souls, bound by something deeper than love.”

And as they stood there, embraced by the cosmic ballet of the stars above and the rhythmic waves below, they realized that their souls had indeed transcended the physical realm. The universe of flesh had faded, leaving behind two souls, dancing to the timeless rhythm of love.
.

Self-love is a journey that can be difficult to navigate. One of the biggest obstacles that many of us face is the pressure to be perfect. We are bombarded with images of “perfect” bodies, “perfect” lives, and “perfect” relationships. It’s easy to get caught up in this idea that we have to be perfect in order to be worthy of love and acceptance. 

But the truth is, perfection is a myth. We are all flawed, and that’s okay. 

In fact, it’s more than okay. Our flaws are what make us unique and interesting. They are the imperfections that make us human. Embracing our flaws and loving ourselves, despite them, is what truly allows us to be confident and authentic. When we accept and love ourselves, we are able to let go of the need to be perfect and instead focus on being our best selves.  Healthy skin give me boosts of confidence and L’oreal Glycolic Acid Serum helps me to achieve that. More context 👇

This video uses just one technique:
🔥✂️ The Match Cut

🎥 Filming

Take a bunch of pictures of the same subject. 

Make sure you have guidelines turned on in your camera.

Make sure you keep the following the same between each shot
1️⃣ Focal length
2️⃣ Distance to camera
3️⃣ Position within camera

💻 Editing

1️⃣ Choose one shot as the reference shot.
2️⃣ For each of the other shots, set the opacity to 50% so you can line it up perfectly.
3️⃣ Add click sounds to help sell the effect

Hi, I’m Qasim, and I’m building a platform to help people migrate to the US while documenting how I go from $0 to $1M—all while traveling the world.

Today started calmly, with a bus ride and some time at the airport lounge to relax and work on this series. But things took a sharp turn in Doha when Shanze realized she had left her green card on the plane!

What followed was a race against time at the transfer desk. If we waited for the green card, we’d miss the flight to Pakistan. With just minutes to spare, we made the tough call to board the flight, hoping the card would somehow follow us.

As the plane took off, the green card hadn’t arrived. What happens next? Stay tuned as the journey unfolds—one challenge at a time.

In this video, we put the model to the test and build all sorts of things. From building Twitter clones, drag-and-drop CRMs, to one-shotting 2D Spider-Man game, Marvel-themed Tetris!

caption:
essential things to know about equity if you’re working at a startup that could quite literally save you a ton of money one day

(none of this is financial advice, please do your own research)

Compare two startup equity paths ⬇️

Scenario 1: Status quo
- You get 100K options
- Strike price: $0.10/share
- You don’t early exercise
- Company grows → $10/share
- Taxable income at exercise:
$9.90 × 100K = $990K
- You owe ~37% income tax = $366K
- You net: ~$624K

Scenario 2: Early exercise
- Same 100K options @ $0.10/share
- You early exercise → pay $10K now
- FMV = strike → no tax owed now
- Company grows → $10/share
- You owe long-term cap gains (15–20%)
- Tax = ~$150K, you net ~$840K

⚠️ Notes:
- Not financial advice — this stuff is nuanced
- You must file an 83(b) if early exercising
- There’s risk: if startup fails, you lose your $10K

(not me filming a very serious video while I’m in line at CVS 🫠💀)

caption:
Tutorial 👇

🎥 Filming

Record 3 different shots using a tripod:
1️⃣ [REAL] throw the hat
2️⃣ [PRETEND] throw the hat - same position as 1st shot but w/o the hat
3️⃣ close up of the hat spinning - attach it to a string so that it spins naturally

💻 Editing
1️⃣ mask out the hat from the close up clip
2️⃣ start with the REAL clip. right after the hat leaves your hand, cut to the PRETEND clip
3️⃣ add the masked out hat. use keyframes to make it start small at first. then come right in front of the camera and then get small again as it hits you in the head.
4️⃣ apply speed ramping

-
-

Virality is dead ✢

In 2019, we lived in the “Attention Economy” where vanity metrics like: 

✶ Views 
✶ Likes 
✶ Comments 

were the defining metrics for success. 
But in 2025 we’re headed towards the “Trust Economy” where the most valuable assets in social media are trust, impact, and community

To build a lasting brand, modern brands need to start thinking more like creators and make content that entertains, educates, and connects 

Don’t get me wrong making content that drives engagement is important but it also has to tell your brand’s story and identity to stay ingrained in a viewers mind.

2️⃣ Pick one topic you’re passionate about and create a freebie (guide, template, checklist) to grow your email list.

caption:
Ep. 4 How much it costs to ATTEND a wedding (as a guest and a bridesmaid)

I actually don’t say yes to all the weddings I’m invited to. I also did not choose bridesmaids until really late because I was too afraid of putting that kind of pressure on anyone. 😳 Attending weddings have very real costs!

I’m genuinely surprised by how high our turnout rate was. For the friends who couldn’t make it, we were absolutely not offended whatsoever. Asking people to take time off, fly internationally, and spend all that money is a lot! 

Have you declined a wedding invite before due to costs or other sticky reasons? 

Have you declined being a bridesmaid or groomsman before? 👀🍵

PS. This concludes our wedding finances deep talks for now. The next wave of posts will be the actual wedding. We will have more wedding finances debriefs after though. Stay tuned!

Here’s how it happens (and it’s more common than you think):

✅ DTC brand scaling fast
✅ Running Shopify + Amazon + their own COD portal
✅ Inventory scattered across 5 manual tools
✅ Order volumes double overnight
❌ No real-time visibility
❌ No auto-routing
❌ No forecasting
= Pure chaos.

We rebuilt their backend using a real AI operations system — not some template dashboard.

caption:
Comment “EDIT” and I’ll send a video tutorial on the technique used in this video: the Match Cut.

More context 👇

This video uses just one technique:
🔥✂️ The Match Cut

🎥 Filming

Take a bunch of pictures of the same subject. 

Make sure you have guidelines turned on in your camera.

Make sure you keep the following the same between each shot
1️⃣ Focal length
2️⃣ Distance to camera
3️⃣ Position within camera

💻 Editing

1️⃣ Choose one shot as the reference shot.
2️⃣ For each of the other shots, set the opacity to 50% so you can line it up perfectly.
3️⃣ Add click sounds to help sell the effect

So McDonald’s recently launched McCrispys

They’re chicken tenders. Who cares?

McDonald’s worked with 100+ small creators

500 million views later, it’s McDonald’s most successful new item launch since the McRib.

Kudos to McDonalds for pioneering this strategy 👏

caption: Who cares if you spend a few lakhs a year on coffee?

You need to get into their heads.🧠

Just knowing basic shit doesn’t help, and that’s the reason your content is not going viral.

You need to get into their emotions feel what they are feeling and that’s how they trust you on their money. 💰 

Just FYI, people do not buy from their rational brain, but from their emotional brain also called limbic system. 

And that you get to know when you understand the psychographics

You can use a Google form, asking 3 to 5 questions to your audience and put it on your stories.
1. What do you want in next one year?
2. What is your long-term vision?
3.  What is stopping you from achieving your goal?
4. What would be the first step you take if there were no struggles?

Get at least 10 to 15 answers and your psychographics are sorted.

Save it & Thank me later ♥️

Self-love is a journey that can be difficult to navigate. One of the biggest obstacles that many of us face is the pressure to be perfect. We are bombarded with images of “perfect” bodies, “perfect” lives, and “perfect” relationships. It’s easy to get caught up in this idea that we have to be perfect in order to be worthy of love and acceptance. 

But the truth is, perfection is a myth. We are all flawed, and that’s okay. 

In fact, it’s more than okay. Our flaws are what make us unique and interesting. They are the imperfections that make us human. Embracing our flaws and loving ourselves, despite them, is what truly allows us to be confident and authentic. When we accept and love ourselves, we are able to let go of the need to be perfect and instead focus on being our best selves.  Healthy skin give me boosts of confidence and L’oreal Glycolic Acid Serum helps me to achieve that. This serum helps me to let go of the need to be “perfect” and focus on being MY best self, because self-love is not about being perfect, it’s about loving ourselves exactly as we are, flaws and all

caption:
- in the heart of Sydney’s twinkling cityscape, Jai and Afsana embarked on an evening that neither would forget. As the setting sun painted the horizon with hues of pink and purple, the two stepped out, elegantly attired. Afsana wore a graceful black dress that flowed like the dark, tranquil waters of the Harbour. Jai, in contrast, wore a sharp black tuxedo, echoing the silhouette of Sydney’s architectural marvels.

The evening began with a candlelit dinner at a rooftop restaurant overlooking the Sydney Opera House. The mellow light from the candles reflected in Afsana’s eyes, revealing a depth that pulled Jai in, much like the vast Australian night sky pulls one into its myriad constellations. Their conversation flowed effortlessly, much like the waters beneath the Harbour Bridge, punctuated with laughter and shared dreams.

As dinner concluded, they took a leisurely walk along the Circular Quay. The cool breeze from the ocean intertwined with the melodies of street musicians, setting a romantic ambiance. With every step, the dazzling lights of the city seemed to fade into the background, replaced by a world only they could perceive.

With the Sydney Tower Eye witnessing their journey from afar, they spoke of dreams, fears, and everything in between. As they walked and talked, it felt as if the universe had slowed its pace just for them, allowing them a moment in eternity.

Under the canopy of the starlit sky, by the shores of the Pacific, they paused. Afsana looked deep into Jai’s eyes and whispered, “Tonight, amidst this vast universe of flesh and concrete, it feels like we’re just two souls, bound by something deeper than love.”

And as they stood there, embraced by the cosmic ballet of the stars above and the rhythmic waves below, they realized that their souls had indeed transcended the physical realm. The universe of flesh had faded, leaving behind two souls, dancing to the timeless rhythm of love.
.

caption: Creator @edmund.tian is here with three easy transitions to help add some flair to your videos within the Edits app! 🤳 ✨ #MadeWithEdits

Comment “EDIT” and I’ll send a video tutorial on the technique used in this video: the Match Cut.

More context 👇

This video uses just one technique:
🔥✂️ The Match Cut

🎥 Filming

Take a bunch of pictures of the same subject. 

Make sure you have guidelines turned on in your camera.

Make sure you keep the following the same between each shot
1️⃣ Focal length
2️⃣ Distance to camera
3️⃣ Position within camera

💻 Editing

1️⃣ Choose one shot as the reference shot.
2️⃣ For each of the other shots, set the opacity to 50% so you can line it up perfectly.
3️⃣ Add click sounds to help sell the effect

-

caption:
This mistake cost us 10 lakhs and 2 months to fix!

It’s very easy to fall into the feature trap early on thinking that more features = better product and better competitive advantage in the market. 

Secondly, we benchmarked too much on what works in the US market thinking that something that works there will work here too. 

But we were wrong about both. 

First product failed, we ended up spending an extra 10 lakhs to reformulate and went behind by 2 months! 

10 lakhs may not sound much but trust me for a young startup like ours we need to think for every 10k we spend. 

Biggest learning : Always start with the customer. Understand their needs deeply and solve their problems. 

When we did just that both our revenues and repeat rates went up

If you’re an aspiring founder, pay attention to Storytelling. It’s highly underrated 

But trust me, this is one thing I put to use all the time - be it pitch meetings, content, or even brand positioning work. 

It’s both art and science and takes practice to get better at (I am still learning too) but once become good at it, it gives you an unfair advantage. 

My top books to learn more are 

1. Storyworthy by Matthew Dicks
2. Contagious by Jonah Berger
3. Building a story brand by Donald Miller 

Stay tuned for the next part! 

If you’d like to talk more about storytelling as a topic, tag me in comments. 

#founder #storytelling #startup #skill #entrepreneur #nuvie #brand #marketing

full recipe now down below 👇🏼 

Ingredients (per bowl):
1 medium banana
3 tbsp milk**
1 tbsp sugar free maple syrup (or other natural sweetener)
1 tbsp yoghurt 

2 tbsp vanilla protein powder
3 tbsp plain flour
1/4 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp cinnamon 

** you made need more/less milk depending on the consistency of your protein powder

Method:
Mash ~3/4 of the banana in a small oven proof dish (reserve the remaining 1/4 to slice for the top). Mix together remaining ingredients. Top with the remaining sliced banana.
Bake @ 180C for 22-25 minutes (skewer should come out clean)

caption:
↓ How to change your self-image ↓ 

Comment ''Self-Esteem'' to get my free self-esteem guide ❤️

When you change your self-image, you change your life. 

My clients have gone from socially anxious, to feeling calm & confident by doing this exact practice & today I am giving it away for free.

So SAVE it for later ❤️

1. Get clear on what negative beliefs you currently carry about yourself. 

Help questions: What am I afraid other think of me? What parts of yourself do you dislike, and why? What am I afraid will happen when I am myself? 

2. Realise that your mind always tries to proof the things it already beliefs. So you don't see a reflection of reality, you see a reflection of your self-image in your outside world. 

3. Reframe the negative beliefs into positive ones.

4. Look for evidence of these new beliefs every day. You self-image (and subconscious mind) can only be rewired through repetition.

5. Stop the narrative of the negative self-image, when it comes up.

DM me ''SELFIMAGE'' if you are ready to overcome your anxious overthinking & build lasting confidence 🔮

Much love,
Linde

i have been sent a lot of DMs about my classic brownies so if you want a full recipe tutorial for this please let me know 

lots of love,

tan x

Oreo Stuffed Brownies Full Recipe
3/4 cup butter
3/4 cup dark chocolate, roughly chopped
1 cup brown sugar
1 cup caster sugar
1 tsp vanilla
3 large eggs
3/4 cup plain flour
1/2 cup cocoa powder
pinch of salt
1 pack classic oreos

Method:
Heat together the butter and the dark chocolate until melted and completely combined. 
Whisk in sugar until fully dissolved 
Whisk in vanilla and egg
Sift and fold through the cocoa, salt & flour
Transfer half the mixture to a line baking tin (20x20cm)
Top with a single layer of whole Oreos
Transfer the remaining brownie mixture over the Oreo layer and gently flatten
Top with extra crushed oreos
Bake @180C for ~25 minutes (less time will make them more fudgy)
Leave aside to cool

Cheesy Potato Gratin Shakshuka 

My go to classic shakshuka recipe just got an upgrade. I’ve added @potato_utopia Four Cheese Potato Gratin to the base, and it completely elevates the dish - rich, cheesy and full of flavour. This new discovery is definitely staying in the regular rotation this winter.

Otherwise recipe can be found below 👇🏼 
Ingredients (serves 3-4 people):
1pkt @potato_utopia Cheese Potato Gratins
2 tbsp olive oil
1 red capsicum, thinly diced
1 medium onion, finely diced
2 garlic cloves, minced
1 tsp chilli powder
2 tsp ground paprika
2 tsp cumin
Salt and pepper, to taste
800g crushed tomatoes
4 eggs

To serve:
1/2 cup crumbled feta cheese
Coriander, finely chopped
1 tsp chilli flakes
4 pieces sourdough bread

Method:
Cook @potato_utopia Four Cheese Potato Gratin as per packet instruction.

Meanwhile, begin cooking the shakshuka base. Heat olive oil over medium heat. Add diced onion and capsicum, and sauté until onion becomes translucent (~5 minutes). Stir in minced garlic, chilli powder, cumin, paprika, salt and pepper. Cook for another minute. Pour in crushed tomatoes and simmer until slightly thickened (~8 minutes).

Once the potato gratin is cooked, gently transfer into the tomato sauce. Create four small holes in the tomato mix and crack in the eggs into each hole.

Cover with a lid until eggs are cooked through to your liking. Garnish with chopped coriander, chilli flakes, feta and serve with toasted sourdough bread.

banana bread recipe 🍌 follow @nicolinanunes for more recipes & motivation

🍌 high protein  🍌 prebiotic 🍌 gut friendly 🍌 fiber rich 🍌 reduce inflammation  🍌 easy to make

INGREDIENTS: → 2 medium overripe bananas → 3 eggs
→ 1/2 cup (120g) of 0% fat Greek yogurt or protein yogurt  → 180g of oat flour (blended oats)
→ 1 and 1/2 tsp baking powder
→ 1 tbsp of cinnamon
→ 30g of walnuts crushed
→ pinch of flaky salt

METHOD:
→ preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) → line a loaf pan with parchment paper
→ in a large bowl mash the bananas until smooth. Whisk in the eggs and Greek yogurt until fully combined
→ add oat flour, baking powder, and cinnamon. Gently mix until a smooth batter forms. Dont overmix
→ add crushed walnuts and spread evenly
→ bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. If the top browns too fast cover with foil! → let it rest in the pan for 10 minutes
→ finish with a pinch of flaky salt

This Cable Looks Normal But Can Hack Your Device In Seconds

The omg cable looks like an ordinary usb charger but it contains a built-in microcontroller that creates a wireless access point.

once plugged in it powers the device like normal but also broadcasts a hidden wifi network. an attacker can connect to that network and remotely control the cable through a browser interface.

they can inject keystrokes log input open applications or execute scripts, just like if they had physical access to your device.

this tool is used in red team operations and security testing to demonstrate how easily trust in hardware can be exploited.

#omgcable #cybersecurity #usbattack #wirelessaccesspoint #ethicalhacking #polinaintech

caption:
Comment CHICKEN and I’ll send you a dm for RECIPE & links 

I didn’t really learn to cook until I was an adult. And I’ve had to teach myself a lot of the Panamanian recipes that I wish I had grown up making, mostly from memory or calling my mom (who, of course, doesn’t measure a thing so her instructions are, “un poquito” or “no mucho”). So the way I cook  might not be perfectly authentic but I I’m learning!

Today I’m making pollo guisado with plátano frito, this was one of my childhood favorites 
😍🥹🇵🇦

🍗 Pollo Guisado (Stovetop Chicken Stew)

Ingredients:
✨1.5–2 lbs boneless, skinless chicken thighs 
✨2 tsp olive or avocado oil 
✨1 tsp oregano, garlic powder, onion powder
✨2 tsp adobo
✨1 onion, diced
✨2 minced cloves of garlic
✨salt to taste
✨1 tbsp tomato paste
✨1 tbsp soy sauce
✨1 packet of sazon
✨2 cups water mixed with 2 tsp Better Than Bouillon chicken
✨veggies of choice (I used tomatoes but red and green bell peppers would be my next choice)
✨1 tbsp ketchup 
✨Handful of chopped cilantro
✨1/2 cup manzanilla olives

Instructions:
Season chicken with adobo, oregano, garlic powder, and onion powder. Sear in hot skillet with oil until browned, then set aside. In the same pan, cook onions until softened,  add garlic cloves, salt, tomato paste, sazon & soy sauce. Let it caramelize for 2 min. Add chicken back in, stir in 2C of water mixed with 2 tsp Better Than Bouillon. Add tomatoes and any veggies you like. Simmer uncovered for 30 min until the sauce thickens. Stir in ketchup, cilantro, and olives, and let it simmer 5  min. Adjust salt to taste.

To make the Platano Frito: when you’re buying your plantains, you have to make sure they are fully green without a hint of yellow, and if you want to keep them green until you’re ready to cook, put them in the fridge or they will ripen and become sweet plantains . Once you’re ready to cook them, just peel them and slice them and fry them in avocado oil until your desired crispiness usually around five minutes.

caption:
Comment SUMMER SALAD and I’ll send you RECIPE and links!

I am going to be so sad when cherries and peaches are out of season because these had been my go to salads all season long! And if you don’t have a grill, then roasting them on the pan with a little bit of honey is the way to go!

Cherry & Peach Summer Stone Fruit Salad

Ingredients
✨Arugula
✨Cherries, sliced
✨Peaches, sliced
✨Feta cheese, cubed(goat cheese or mozzarella works)
✨Prosciutto
✨Honey or balsamic glaze for drizzling
✨Flaky salt

Vinaigrette
✨3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil
✨1 ½ tablespoons white wine vinegar
✨1 teaspoon whole grain mustard
✨1 teaspoon honey
✨¼ teaspoon salt (adjust to taste)
✨⅛ teaspoon black pepper

Slice peaches and caramelize them in a pan with olive oil and honey. Crisp the prosciutto in the air fryer for 5 minutes at 400°F. In a bowl, whisk together vinegar, olive oil, mustard, honey, salt, and pepper for the vinaigrette, then toss in the arugula to coat. Assemble the salad with arugula, peaches, cherries, feta, and prosciutto. Drizzle with honey or balsamic glaze and finish with flaky salt.

Marinated Cheddarella
Ingredients for zesty vinaigrette 
✨¼ cup olive oil
✨1 tbsp red wine vinegar 
✨1 tsp Dijon mustard 
✨1 garlic clove, finely grated or smashed
✨½ tsp crushed red pepper flakes 
✨1 tsp dried oregano
✨1 tsp dried basil or Italian seasoning
✨Zest of ½ lemon
✨1/8 tsp salt to taste

This is my take on the viral Turkish pasta! I love the contrast of the cool garlicky yogurt with the warm Smokey butter. Plus, it’s super easy to prep the ground beef ahead of time so when you’re ready to eat, it comes together fast for an easy and delicious  lunch or dinner.

Turkish Pasta
✨cooked pasta of choice(I toss mine in garlicky butter)
✨garlicky yogurt
✨seasoned ground beef (I use lean)
✨smoked butter sauce
✨cherry tomatoes
✨fresh parsley
✨sumac onions
Layer pasta, garlicky yogurt, ground beef, tomatoes and fresh parsley  then drizzle with butter sauce. Top with sumac onions and enjoy! 

Seasoned Ground Beef
✨1lb lean grass fed ground beef 
✨1/2 tablespoon avocado oil
✨1 small onion, finely minced 
✨2 cloves garlic, minced
✨2 green onions, chopped
✨1 teaspoon garlic powder & onion powder 
✨1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika 
✨1 tablespoon soy sauce
Sauté oil and onion until translucent. Add garlic, green onions, and ground beef. Once browned, stir in seasonings and soy sauce. Cook until no longer pink. Taste and adjust salt. I always keep this meal prepped in my fridge because I use it for so many quick lunches throughout the week, including my cottage cheese bowls!

Garlicky Yogurt sauce (1 serving)
✨1/2 cup Greek yogurt
✨1 clove of garlic zested 
✨juice of 1/2 lemon
✨salt to taste 
Combine all of the ingredients and let sit for a few minutes to mellow out the garlic flavor. Make sure you taste it because it usually needs more salt than you think it does!

Smoked butter sauce
✨1 teaspoon tomato paste 
✨1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika
✨1/2 teaspoon red chili flakes
✨2 Tablespoons butter 
Toast tomato paste, paprika, and chili flakes over medium heat for 1 min, stirring often. Add butter and simmer on low for 1 min.

Sumac onions 
✨1 small red onion thinly sliced
✨juice of 2 lemons
✨1 Tablespoon sumac 
Combine and marinate for as long as possible

Travel days with the whole family can feel super exhausting so the last thing we want to do when we arrive at our destination is wait around for luggage, not to mention the nightmare it would be if they got delayed or lost so that’s why we are carry-on only family! Here are my best tips if you would also like to travel with carry-on only:

1.	Plan every outfit down to the jewelry and shoes. It keeps things minimal and prevents overpacking.
2.	We all get 2 pairs of shoes total: we wear the bulkier pair (usually dinner shoes) on the plane and pack either water shoes or sandals.
3.	Repeat the travel outfit. Whatever we wear on the flight there is the same outfit we wear home. I’ll either send it to the resort laundry or wash it in the shower and hang to dry.
4.	Wear your bulky items. I always wear my bulkiest shoes and layers to the airport to save bag space.
5.	Use packing cubes to compress and organize. They don’t just keep things neat, they squeeze everything down so it actually fits.
6.	Skip packing sunscreen. We always buy it at the destination since we use the whole can anyway.
7.	Keep liquids in mini sizes. I also save jars from mini samples and refill them with my own face creams to avoid bringing full size products. 
8.	For tropical trips, make swimwear do double duty. Bathing suits and cover ups are our daytime outfits, and I pack one nice dinner outfit each.
9.	Keep activities simple. I used to pack a million things and learned they barely get touched. A fully charged iPad and headphones do the trick, we took the iPads away a week before so my kids were extra excited on travel day.
10.	Give kids their own backpack. It carries some of their clothes, water shoes, a snack, and a few small things they’re excited about, which keeps their essentials organized and lightens my bag.
11. Don’t forget to drink your electrolytes! Staying hydrated will solve everything else 🤣🤣

✈️ Are you team carry on only or do you always check a bag for family trips?

If you have never had banana pudding, this is a classic no bake dessert and staple in the south and you can find it at a lot of bbq restaurants or family cookouts! I learned how to make it because it’s my husband’s absolute favorite dessert!

The best Banana pudding 
✨1 box(3.4 oz)  of French vanilla pudding
✨1 box(3.4oz)  of banana cream pudding
✨2 cups of milk
✨1 (8oz) block of cream cheese 
✨1 (14oz) can condensed milk
✨2 cups of homemade whipped cream(1 c for the filling & 1 cup for the topping) 
✨4 boxes (5.3oz) of walkers cookies
✨6 bananas sliced 
✨brown sugar for garnish (optional) 

Homemade whipped cream 
✨2 cups of heavy whipping cream
✨1/2 cup of powdered sugar
✨1 teaspoon vanilla extract 

Blend milk & pudding mix with and refrigerate. In another bowl, whip heavy cream, powdered sugar, and vanilla until stiff peaks form. Mix cream cheese and condensed milk until smooth, then fold in half the whipped cream. Combine with the pudding mixture. 

Layer the bottom of a baking dish with Pudding >cookies > pudding > bananas > pudding > whipped cream then Garnish with crumbled cookies and bananas, sprinkle with sugar, and optionally brûlée the bananas. 

Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.

In the video I only made half of the recipe above, so if you’re making the full recipe then you will need a 13x9x2 baking dish.

This is my take on a panzanella salad, you have to make this at least once this summer!! It’s the perfect way to use up stale bread, and the combo of juicy peaches, sweet cherries, and crispy garlicky bread is just unreal. Trust me, you’ll be hooked!

Peach & Cherry Panzanella Salad
✨1 baguette, torn
✨evoo
✨1 garlic clove 
✨1 peach, cubed
✨1 cup cherries, halved + pitted
✨1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved
✨1 small shallot, thinly sliced
✨Salt, garlic powder, Parmesan cheese to season bread
✨Stracciatella, chili flakes, basil for garnish

Dressing
✨Tomato juice (from salted tomatoes)
✨Minced toasted garlic
✨1 tbsp minced shallot
✨1/2 tsp Dijon
✨1/4 cup champagne vinegar
✨1 tbsp balsamic
✨1/2 cup olive oil
✨1/2 tsp salt, 1/4 tsp pepper

Instructions
1.	Salt the tomatoes and place them in a strainer over a bowl. Let the juices collect underneath.you’ll be using it for the dressing!
 2.	Heat olive oil in a pan with the garlic clove. Once garlic is golden, remove and set aside. Add bread chunks and toast until crispy. Add more oil if needed. At the end, season with salt, garlic powder, and Parmesan. (You can also bake the bread at 375°F for 10-15 minutes, just cut the bread with the EVOO and all the spices, and then bake tossing halfway)
3.	Prep produce, cube the peach, pit and halve cherries, slice shallot.
4.	Make dressing by tossing all dressing ingredients together in the same bowl that the juice from the tomatoes collected.
5.	Combine toasted bread, tomatoes, peach, cherries, shallots Add dressing and toss well. 
Let sit for 5-10 minutes then Top with stracciatella, chili flakes, and fresh basil and enjoy! 
Note: if you cut your bread into larger chunks, it stays good much longer. This was good three hours later!

I’m not really one to go out looking for a burger, and if I do- it’s always going to be a smash burger. I just loooove thin patties with crispy edges!! 

for the longest time, I was supernova’s biggest cheerleader, it’s honestly an impeccable burger and every time i’m in Soho, it’s a battle every time not to pop over and pick up their burger. 

BUT, @dumboparis just opened a location in London, and I’ve always heard so much about it- so when I was in London for the day, I made sure to try it. 

It honestly blew me away. It’s the same price as Supernova but is much bigger and heftier. The crispy patties are right on par, but there’s this lovely smoky and deeply meaty flavor that’s quite addicting. I loved the pickles in there because it cut through some of that smokiness and added just a really balanced mouthfeel. The sauce was gorgeous, cheese perfectly melted, and the bun was glorious. I HATE brioche buns for burgers, I always find them too sweet but I LOVE a potato bun. I was super surprised to hear this was a mix between a potato & brioche! Super soft but structurally sound- and with none of the sickly sweetness that traditional brioche buns can have. DELISH! 

What really took the cake was the fact that their fries were sooooo much better. They’re twice fried and have that craggly crispy coating on the outside which are unreal. Supernova’s fries are very bad and I never get them. The only downer was the sauce Dumbo gave was really weird and quite unpleasant, but I prefer plain ketchup anyways so it’s not the end of the world- but seriously the sauce is very weird and I need someone to agree with me so I don’t feel crazy. 

10/10 recommend, try to get there before 5:30 before the employed people leave their jobs and run here for a burger 😸

Where you put the camera MATTERS 👇🏻

When you watch a movie, nothing about the way you feel is an accident…

The placement of the camera tells a story in itself.

But it’s not obvious which ones to choose to tell the right story, so let me tell you:

Wide, centred shot: Achieves a sense of peace and balance 

Close up: heightens connection to the subject and immerses in the emotion of the scene 

High angle: Makes the subject seem weaker and less powerful 

Low angle: The opposite - the subject feels powerful and in control

Object in foreground/depth: Adds extra context or feels like the viewer is watching something private 

Save this video to try some of these in your next story!

#visualstorytelling #cinematicfeel #contenttips #creatorclass #filmmaking #storytellingvisual

AI Automation vs AI Agent, clearly explained!
 
The future is Agentic AI, and it’s because traditional automation has some major limitations...👇
 
1) Linear execution paths only.
↳ Automation follows predefined steps without deviation, making it brittle when facing unexpected situations.
 
2) Rule-based decision making.
↳ If something wasn’t in the rulebook, automation simply fails or produces nonsense.
 
3) Static knowledge and capabilities.
↳ Once deployed, traditional automation doesn’t improve without human intervention.
 
4) Limited context understanding.
↳ Automation processes data but doesn’t grasp what it’s actually doing or why.
 
AI Agents solves these problems.
 
Think of it like this:
 
Step 1) Start with a goal, not a procedure.
↳ “Achieve this outcome” vs “Follow these exact steps”
 
Step 2) Observe the environment and gather relevant information.
↳ Agents actively seek what they need rather than just using what they’re given.
 
Step 3) Plan the approach, considering multiple strategies.
↳ Unlike automation, this planning adapts to each unique situation.
 
Step 4) Make smart decisions at key moments:
↳ Act now? Get more information? Change tactics?
 
Step 5) After acting, evaluate success.
↳ Did it work? Why or why not?
 
Step 6) Learn from experience through feedback loops.
↳ This creates continuous improvement without programming updates.
 
The bottom line: Automation executes tasks. Agents solve problems.
 
Both have their place.
 
Over to you: Which approach fits your specific needs?

Everybody has to start somewhere, and it’s usually by imitating their influences… let me explain👇🏻

I had a big creator take one of my old videos out of context to say that creators should “steal now, and tweak later” - which I did say. 

But here’s the context…

Being a creator is hard. And everyone has to start somewhere, and that usually means looking up to your influences, and imitating them until you start to come up with your own ideas. 

It’s a right of passage of being any creative that you go through the imitation phase, until you become skilled enough to have your own original ideas.

But - let’s be honest, nothing is really original. Everything has been done before, and you’re not wrong for borrowing ideas when you are creating videos. 

So keep creating, and don’t be afraid to try to be like your influences - until you have nailed your own style.

Here’s 5 engaging cinematic shots for your content 👇🏻

1. Depth Shot: shooting with something in the foreground with a low f stop can add a really interesting depth effect.

2. Top-down/birds eye view shot: Another interesting way to add context of the scene from above.

3. Close up shot: Adding a bit more detail of what is specifically happening in the scene. Use a low aperture for a creamy blur in the background. 

4. Object in foreground shot: Bring attention to another element of the scene, where the story or movement continues in the background. 

5. Object isolation shot: Another angle of close up shot, that gives more detail to a specific object in the shot.

This was one of the best things I made with tomato last year so it deserved a reintroduction!If you’ve never had tomato pie, this is your sign. It’s creamy, tangy, and the caramelized onions take it to another level! Save this for the next time you need to bring a dish to a summer cookout!

Southern Tomato Pie
Ingredients
✨1 store bought pie crust
✨4 to 5 tomatoes
✨6 oz shredded cheddar cheese
✨1/2 cup mayonnaise
✨1/2 cup sour cream
✨1/4 teaspoon garlic powder
✨1/4 teaspoon chives
✨1 tablespoon minced chipotle peppers (or use jalapeños to make it spicy)
✨2 tablespoons whole grain mustard
✨Salt and pepper to taste

Caramelized Onions
✨1 sweet yellow onion, thinly sliced
✨1 tablespoon olive oil
✨1 tablespoon butter
✨1 teaspoon sugar
✨Pinch of salt

Instructions
1.	Preheat your oven to 350°F.
2.	Press the pie crust into a baking dish, prick the bottom then Bake for 10 minutes.
3.	Slice the tomatoes, sprinkle with salt, and let them sit on paper towels to drain.
4.	Make caramelized onions by thinly slicing them cooking with olive oil, butter, and sugar over medium heat for about 20 minutes until golden. Add a pinch of salt at the end.
5.	In a bowl combine cheese, mayo, sour cream, garlic powder, chives, chipotle peppers, salt, pepper, and caramelized onions.
6.	Spread the mustard on the bottom of the baked pie crust, sprinkle a thin layer of shredded cheese, then the sliced tomatoes, then the cheese mixture.
7.	Bake for 25 minutes, then broil for 2-3 min until the top is golden.
8.	Let it cool for 15 minutes before slicing.
Enjoy!!

The biggest lie women are sold? That you can out-train a bad diet! ❤️‍🩹

When I was overweight, I thought my problem was discipline. So I worked out harder!
6–7 days a week. HIIT. Cardio. Hours at the gym.
And guess what? I was exhausted, frustrated… and my body barely changed

My real glow up happened when I stopped punishing myself and started fueling myself:

I ate foods I loved, not “diet foods” that left me starving
I cut back to 3–4 solid workouts a week
I prioritized protein, healthy fats & fiber
I stopped skipping breakfast + stopped living on snacks
I built satisfying, hormone-friendly meals
I swapped hours of cardio for walks
I started training less and LIVING more!! ✨

I don’t have the most disciplined body in the room but I have the happiest one! So if you’re stuck thinking you just need “more”, more workouts, more rules, more discipline, hear me: You don’t need more, you need better!

This is one of those meals that come together super fast, great for those days when you just don’t feel like cooking, but want something that your whole family will enjoy!

Viral Million dollar Spaghetti 
Ingredients
For the meat sauce:
✨2 pounds ground beef
✨1 whole sweet onion, diced
✨ 5 cloves garlic, minced
✨ 1 tablespoon low-sodium soy sauce
✨ Salt and black pepper, to taste
✨ 1 jar 28oz marinara sauce (or 2 15.5 oz jars)
✨ 2 cups chopped fresh spinach

For the Alfredo sauce:
✨3 cups heavy cream
✨80 g freshly grated Parmesan cheese (about 1 cup)
✨½ block (4 oz) cream cheese
✨1 stick butter
✨ 3 garlic cloves, zested or finely grated
✨Salt and pepper, to taste

For the pasta:
✨ 1 pound spaghetti
✨Salt (for pasta water)

For topping:
✨2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
✨1 cup shredded cheddar cheese

Instructions
1.	Preheat your oven to 375°F.
2.	Make the meat sauce:
In a large skillet or Dutch oven over medium-high heat, brown the ground beef. Add diced onion and cook until soft. Stir in the garlic and cook for 1 minute.
Season with soy sauce, salt, and pepper. Pour in marinara sauce and simmer on low. Stir in the chopped spinach during the last few minutes of simmering until wilted. Remove from heat.
3.	Cook the spaghetti:
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Cook the spaghetti 1 minute under al dente. Drain and set aside.
4.	Make the Alfredo sauce:
In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Add garlic zest and stir for 30 seconds. Pour in heavy cream and bring to a gentle simmer. Stir in cream cheese until smooth, then add Parmesan. Season with salt and pepper and simmer until slightly thickened.
5.	Assemble the bake:
In a 9x13 baking dish, combine spaghetti with Alfredo sauce. Spread meat sauce evenly over top.
Sprinkle with mozzarella and cheddar.
6.	Bake:
Bake uncovered for 12–15 minutes, until cheese is melted and bubbly. Rest for 5 minutes, then serve.

Cherry Tart with whipped goat cheese 
✨puff pastry 
✨1 egg for egg wash
✨ whipped goat cheese (recipe below)
✨2 bags of cherries 
✨chopped pistachios for garnish 
✨ honey for drizzling 

Preheat your oven to 400°F. Roll out the puff pastry into a circle on a baking sheet and fold the edges in. Score a circle about an inch from the edge, then prick the inner section with a fork and brush it with egg wash. Bake for 25–30 minutes until golden, then remove and gently press down the center. Spread with whipped goat cheese, top with halved pitted cherries, sprinkle with crushed pistachios, and finish with a drizzle of honey. Enjoy!!

Whipped got cheese
✨8 oz goat cheese
✨4 oz mascarpone or cream cheese
✨1/4 cup powder sugar(or 2Tablespoons of honey)
✨1 Tablespoon lemon juice 
✨splash of milk to thin it out 

Blend all ingredients in a food processor. If you’re using a blender you may need to use extra milk to thin it out. I def recommend using a food processor if you have it for a less runny consistency.

Vodka Pesto Swirl Pizza Recipe
Pizza
✨1 ball pizza dough (12”)
✨1 cup shredded mozzarella
✨1/2 cup fontina (optional)
✨vodka sauce
✨pistachio pesto 

Spicy Vodka Sauce
✨1 tbsp olive oil
✨1 tbsp butter
✨2 garlic cloves, minced
✨½ tsp red pepper flakes
✨2 tbsp tomato paste
✨¼ cup vodka(optional)
✨¾ cup heavy cream
✨3 tbsp grated Parmesan
✨Salt, to taste

Pistachio Pesto
✨1 cup basil
✨1 garlic clove
✨¼ cup pistachios
✨¼ cup Parmesan
✨Juice of ½ lemon
✨¼ tsp salt
✨⅓ cup olive oil

1. Preheat Ninja pizza oven (Neapolitan setting)
2. Blend pesto ingredients until smooth
3. For sauce: sauté garlic + red pepper in oil, add tomato paste, cook 1 min
4. Stir in vodka, reduce, then add cream, butter, cheese, salt and simmer until thick
5. Stretch dough, spread a thin layer of vodka at sauce, add mozzarella
6. Bake for 3 min
7. Finish with swirl of vodka sauce and pesto

Note: you could also use vodka sauce from a jar to save time, but don’t skip on the homemade pesto!

Coconut Shrimp with Yuca Frita & Mojo Sauce

Coconut Shrimp
✨1 lb shrimp, peeled and deveined
✨1 cup flour seasoned with garlic salt and paprika 
✨Coconut oil, for frying

Wet batter:
✨1 cup all-purpose flour
✨¾ cup club soda
✨½ tsp salt
✨¼ tsp baking soda
✨¼ tsp paprika

Dry Coating
✨1 cup panko crumbs
✨1 cup coconut shavings (you can use either sweet or unsweet)
✨Garlic salt, to taste
✨Paprika, to taste

Instructions:
Season the flour with garlic salt and paprika. In another bowl, whisk together the wet batter ingredients. In a third bowl, mix the panko and coconut flakes and season with the same spices. Dredge shrimp in the flour, dip in the batter, then coat in the coconut-panko mixture. Let it sit in the fridge for 5 to 10 minutes then Fry in hot coconut oil until golden, 2–3 minutes per side. Drain on paper towels. I like to add a couple pieces of raw carrot to the oil to keep it clean. This allows me to use the same oil for a few batches without anything burning!

Yuca Frita:
Boil frozen yuca in salted water for 10–15 minutes, until fork-tender. Drain, let cool slightly, Remove the rind in center then slice into thick fries. Fry in hot avocado oil until golden and crispy(about 4min per side) Sprinkle with salt and serve immediately.

Mojo Sauce
✨1 small bunch cilantro
✨4–5 garlic cloves
✨¼–½ cup extra virgin olive oil
✨Salt to taste

Blend everything, Taste and adjust salt or oil if needed.
You can mix with mayo for a creamy dipping sauce

The perfect burger does exist but you must put it inside of a taco shell! The edges get nice and crispy and you get so much more of the melted cheese with caramelized onion flavor and don’t get me started on the truffle mayo!! You’ll want to put on everything! These smash burger tacos are seriously on another level and  I served them with homemade plátano fries! 

Don’t forget to follow me for more easy recipes like this 🥰

Truffle Smash Burger Tacos
✨ 1 lb 80/20 ground beef
✨ 8 tortillas (I used almond flour tortillas)
✨ Cheese of choice (I used truffle Monterey Jack from Trader Joe’s)
✨ Arugula
✨ Caramelized onions (see below)
✨ Homemade truffle mayo (recipe below)

For the caramelized onions:
✨ 1 yellow sweet onion, thinly sliced
✨ 1 tbsp olive oil
✨ 1 tbsp balsamic vinegar
✨ 1 tsp low-sodium soy sauce
✨ Salt & pepper to taste

Sauté onions in evoo over medium low heat for 10 minutes, stir in balsamic vinegar, soy sauce, & salt. Let caramelize for 20-30 min until jammy. Press thin layers of ground beef onto tortillas using parchment paper and a rolling pin. Cook meat side down until crispy, then flip to toast the tortilla. Add cheese to melt and assemble w rest of ingredients

Truffle Mayo
✨ 3 tbsp mayonnaise
✨ ¼ tsp onion powder
✨ ½ garlic clove, finely grated
✨ Pinch of black pepper
✨ 2 tsp finely grated Parmesan
✨ ½ tsp Dijon mustard
✨ ½ tsp white wine vinegar
✨ 1 tsp truffle oil (start with ½ tsp, taste, and adjust)

Plátano Fries
To make them, peel and slice a green plantain into strips. Heat avocado oil in a pan over medium-high heat until it shimmers, it’s ready when the plantains start to sizzle as they hit the oil. Fry in batches until golden and crispy, then transfer to a paper towel lined plate and sprinkle with salt while they’re still hot.

The quantum countdown is a call for preparation, not panic. While no current quantum computer can break our encryption, the long-term threat is real.

NIST has now finalized the first Post-Quantum Cryptography (PQC) standards, such as CRYSTALS-Kyber, to proactively secure our data for decades to come. This isn’t a race against a sudden threat, it’s a foundational shift to future-proof our digital data.

this was BY far one of the best days I’ve had in a long time!! We had gone out a little later than expected so we were all a little queasy this morning and we had a boat cruise booked for 10 AM. I’m already prone to motion sickness so I was quite nervous but honestly I took a motion sickness tablet and I was totally fine! 

If you’re in Paros you HAVE to do this boat tour!! It’s at @argoparos and was definitely one of the highlights! It’s 4-5 hours long, there’s 4 stops with lots of swimming and playing, some really delicious food, flowing drinks, good music, awesome crew, and a really nice boat! 

Not sponsored or gifted, we just loved it SO much- it’s also a new family owned business so i’m so glad we got to support a local business! 

For our night out, we headed to Naousa and we went to Linardo @linardoofficial and honestly it was so fun LOL- the DJ played bangers all night long, the drinks weren’t that expensive, and everyone was dancing a lot. Just a heads-up that there’s a lot of smoking inside so if you’re sensitive to that- it might not be the best! 

But WOW! what a day and night, we ended up staying for the sunrise and got home at 8 am… which you can imagine how it ended 😝 

best holiday ever!

caption:
There’s no better time to have a conversation and reconnect with your loved ones than when you’re on a plane with zero distractions ✈️🗣️

caption:
worrying about something that hasn’t happened yet, (that may not even happen) or a hypothetical situation, although sometimes unavoidable, is an energy drainer 🥹

I know this is obvious, and I know we often cannot help it (I’ve been there 1,000,000 times honestly) !!! but repeating things like this, or the quote ‘it is what it is’ really helps me to ground myself, snap out of the overthinking and rationalise my thoughts 

what will be will be, and me worrying will not change the outcome 

when you worry, the suffering happens twice: first in your mind, as you imagine yourself in the worst-case scenarios, and then potentially again if the situation actually unfolds !! but more often than not, the ‘worst case scenrsrio’ rarely ever happens, meaning you’ve endured all that emotional stress for nothing !! 

worrying is just stealing your peace from the present over something uncertain in the future

we spent two days in Kusadasi where we went to the most wonderful beaches and checked out the national park (which by the way is stunning). 

I knew I wanted to eat a whole grilled fish while we were on the coast as it’s a regional specialty and I figured it wouldn’t be as good in Cappadocia where we were going next. The fish is super fresh over here, and they’re especially known for their sea bass and sea bream. 

Sea bass is a flakier, lighter fish while sea bream is a meatier firmer fish. While bream is better suited for grilling, I prefer the lighter flakier texture of bass. It’s harder to grill, but I figured if they do it well, that’s how I know it’s really good! 

And WOW!! They delivered mega. It was perfectly seasoned and just the right amount of salty to bring out the natural sweetness of the fish. The skin was crispy and completely intact, and the flesh was juicy and had that lovely glassy sheen to it- a marker of perfectly cooked fish. Flaky and melt in your mouth, there was no squeaky rubber feeling. Honestly there’s nothing better than perfectly cooked white fish. Definitely recommend this place! It’s called Fish Fish Balikçi 😋

google reviews honestly put me through it while we were in Cappadocia!! I usually pride myself on being able to sift through reviews and pick really good restaurants, but it felt like every sub par and expensive place had 4.8+ ratings for the most mediocre food. BUT! there were a few gems, and Tast of Moms in Goreme was a lovely family-run restaurant specializing in vegetarian gozleme. 

We’re in the Anatolia region of Türkiye which is known for its flour and wheat based dishes, and gozleme is one of their regional specialities. It’s a flaky flatbread that is very similar to a paratha but slightly less flay. It almost felt like a cross between a tortilla and paratha! 

Khadin is the woman behind the magic and she turned her family home into a restaurant that specializes in gozleme. She was such a whizz with the rolling pin and her technical skill was out of this world, I was in awe watching. It’s truly seeing masters at their craft that reignite my passion for cooking- it’s so humbling to watch. 

Definitely go check this place out it’s amazing! 

#lailaspantry #chef #turkiye #turkey #gozleme #turkishfood #cappadoci̇a

caption:
We’ve been in Cappadocia for the last few days and while it’s the most gorgeous place I’ve ever been, the food here has definitely been much more expensive and more underwhelming than the rest of the cities we’ve visited in Türkiye.

But, a very kind Turkish follower sent me the name of this restaurant and recommended it since it’s very local and authentic. It’s a little outside Goreme which helps the price and taste for sure!! It’s called Fatima ‘nin sofrasi and it’s tucked away in an alley and the staff are soooo kind and helpful. 

We got an assortment regional foods including manti, juicy meatballs, and pottery kebab. I always love how fresh and light everything feels, even though it’s a lot of meat usually. I would definitely recommend the manti, juicy meatball, vine leaves, and pottery kebab. 

Honestly 10/10!!!

chocolate balls recipe 🤎 follow @nicolinanunes for more recipes & motivation

🤎 high protein  🤎 gut friendly 🤎 no bake 🤎 PMS friendly 🤎 reduce inflammation  🤎 easy to make

INGREDIENTS: → 20g peanut butter → 20g sugar free maple syrup → 40ml milk → 40g protein powder → 30g 100% cocoa powder → 10g dark chocolate (for coating) → flaky salt to taste

METHOD: → in a bowl, mix peanut butter, maple syrup and milk → add protein powder and cocoa powder. mix until smooth → spread into a container lined with parchment paper → freeze for 1–2 hours until solid and fudgy → scoop and shape into small balls → melt dark chocolate and dip each ball → sprinkle with flaky salt and freeze for 5 minutes to set

Your pursuit of getting people to like you, is actually the thing wrecking your confidence.

I was lost in anxiety, overthinking, and harsh inner criticism. 

But let me tell you the truth: The problem isn’t people disliking you, it is you thinking they SHOULD like you.

How can you ever feel free to be yourself, follow your passions, and share your voice if you are paralyzed by the idea of others disliking you..

I will tell you the answer: You can’t. 

So take this as your reminder to get my to yourself and connect with what IS important. 
1. Being your true self

Here is a harsh truth: You are not going to find lasting happiness in perfecting your appearance. 😅

Yess looking pretty feels good (I also love to dress up) 💅

But the moment you put your self-worth in how you look, looking pretty will become a never ending pursuit.

You will always feel like just losing a few pounds, a new outfit, that new beauty product, or getting more external validation will make you feel better

While in reality, the thing that will actually make you feel good about yourself, is not how you look, it is knowing and loving who you truly are (behind the appearance). ✨

Because there is SO much more that makes you beautiful than just your appearance. ♥️

This is why my coaching has never focussed on building confidence in your appearance. As confidence goes much deeper, your appearance changes, your self-worth shouldn’t. 

I help women feel confident in who they are, and what they can achieve in this lifetime. 

And the funny thing is, the moment you feel confident in who you are, you also grow more confident in your appearance (as a bi-product of the inner work you have done)

June 16th I am re-opening the doors for Return To Inner Confidence. Trust me, you want to enter this space 🌹

With much love,
Your Confidence Coach, Melinde.

Life is too short to stay small for someone who will never allow themselves to shine. 🫶✨

Show this post some ♥️ if it resonated! 

If you are anything like me, and supporting others is one of your core values, you likely won’t understand why some people do not want the best for you.

Tbh I used to struggle with understanding this as well. 

But the reality isn’t that they don’t want the best for you (they often do!), the reality is that your greatness feels like a threat to them. And this often happens all subconsciously. 

So no, most people do not want to hold you back consciously, but subconsciosuly they are trying to protect themselves from discomfort. 

So let them walk their journey, send them love and hopefully they also will allow themselves to shine.

And you, just focus on yourself and surround yourself with the people who DO love to see you shine. 

With much love,
Your Confidence Coach, Mel.

Here is the crazy part...😅

What you fear others are judging you for, you already judge yourself for. 😶

You only fear what you already believe. 

So if you fear others do not like you, you believe YOU are difficult to like. 

So the problem is not their judgement, it is what you think about yourself. 

A person who truly beliefs they are fun, aren’t going to constantly worry if others find them fun. 

This truth really was the start of my confidence journey, and now I am teaching it to you July 23rd. 🥰

I went from having a social anxiety disorder, constantly fearing judgement and trying to guess what others were thinking...

... To being confident in who I am, even when others doubt me ♥️

This shift took me 3 years, and for the last 2 years I have been guiding others to do it in as little as 2/3 months!

On July 23rd I am hosting a Free Masterclass where I will teach you how to make the same transformation!

Sign-ups will open up this week. ✨🌹

With much love,
Melinde

Tiramisu brownies ☕️☕️

After quite a few attempts, I am actually obsessed with how these turned out.

This twist has been all over my fyp recently so take this as your sign to try them. 

comment ‘tiramisu’ to be sent the full recipe!!

lots of love,

tan x

FULL RECIPE:

Brownie base:
3/4 cup butter
1/2 cup dark chocolate, roughly chopped
1 cup brown sugar
1 cup caster sugar
2 tsp instant coffee powder (optional)
1 tsp vanilla
3 eggs
3/4 cup plain flour
2/3 cup cocoa powder
pinch of salt

Method:
Heat together the butter and dark chocolate until melted and completely combined. 
Whisk in sugar and instant coffee until dissolved 
Whisk in vanilla and egg
Sift and fold through the cocoa & flour. Then through the choc chips
Transfer to a line baking tin (20x20cm)
Bake @180C for ~25minutes (less time will make them more fudgy)
Leave aside to cool 

Marscapone cream:
250g marscapone 
1 cup heavy whipping cream
1/3 cup powdered icing sugar

Using electric mixer, whisk the whipping cream and sugar until soft peaks form. Add in mascarpone and beat until thickened (don’t over mix). Set aisde

Sponge finger layer:
1 cup warm water
2 tbsp instant coffee
12-15 savoiardi biscuits

Dissolve the instant coffee in the warm water. Lightly dip the ladyfinger on each side (don’t soak as will become mushy and fall apart easily)
Layer the lady fingers over the brownie base, followed by the mascarpone cream.

Leave to chill for 4 hours or overnight before sifting cocoa powder on top

Chocolate espresso sauce (optional to serve):
1 cup dark chocolate
1 tbsp instant coffee
1 tbsp heavy cream

Melt chocolate before stiring in the cream and coffee

I couldn't get into every little detail because the video was already too long. Here's more:

1- The 'funny' friend
They're trying to be funny, but always at your expense. They will make fun of your clothes, your family, your personality publicly but will brush it aside as a joke. They also publicly mention things you've told them in private and pretend to 'forget'. This is their way of feeling like the superior one in your relationship.

2- The clingy (manipulative) friend. This friend confides in you all the time, dumps all their emotion baggage on you and it just never stops. It is always about them. If you try to establish boundaries, you're made to feel guilty because you are all they have, the only person who is there for them. So you feel trapped and stay in this friendship because there is no way to escape it without you looking like the bad person. They will also try to slowly isolate you from your other friends because they want to be the center of your attention. Plus they are ALWAYS the victim in all of their other friendships (key point).

3- Your friend who is friends with your bullies/people who have genuinely, objectively harmed you. They care more about their social status, they want to cause no drama and want to stay friends with your bullies. They also hang out with those people because they don't have 'a choice'.

Bonus #4: the friend who ONLY gossips whenever you guys meet!!!
