caption: Fit check 🫧

For 99% of people— especially if you’re ramping up your use with AI— one tool is enough. If I were you, I’d spend less time worrying about what TOOL to use and more time worrying about how to get the most out of the 1 tool you need to master. 

Don’t overcomplicate it! Your job is easier than you think. 

Keep in mind that all those other tools you see are leveraging OpenAI’s API (literally pulling in ChatGPT’s brain) and passing along their costs to you. 

Of course, it’s worth noting that many AI tools out there do things ChatGPT can’t do, or that they do them within an integrated UI/UX that is so much better for a specific use case that it’s worth going for that. But again, I’m talking about the 99% case. 

Put it this way— if you haven’t even used ChatGPT Deep Research yet, don’t ask me about what other tools you should be using 😉

Can’t wait to get roasted in the comments 💕💕💕💕

People always ask: “Cat, why not just live in SF?”
Here’s why👇

In the Bay, everyone’s in tech.
Smart folks. Big ideas. Same lens.
Same jargon. Same blind spots.
“We’ll solve the world with this app.”
Cool. But what if the problem isn’t an app problem?
What if it needs a story? A soul? A different angle?

That’s where LA comes in.
In LA, conversations are about narrative, aura, the vibe.
In SF, it’s product-market fit and AI optimization.

Alone, each city is powerful.
Together, they’re a superpower.

So yeah, the commute gets tiring.
But it keeps me sharp.
Rooted in reality.
And human, above all.

That’s how I make content about AI—
Not for engineers.
For everyone else. 💌

5 ESSENTIAL shots for VISUAL STORYTELLING 👇🏻 

establishing shot: where the scene is taking place, giving the context

medium close up on subject: introduce more of the subject and what they are doing in the scene

foreground focus close up: drawing attention to objects of meaning and focus within the scene, emphasises story continuing in the background 

over the shoulder: an intimate almost pov view of a specific moment or action 

scene transition: movement out of the scene to indicate a scene change

try a few of these out in your videos!

It’s a rare occasion that we have leftover steak in the fridge, but when we do, my favorite thing is to turn it into a yummy sandwich! And this one did not disappoint!

Don’t forget to hit the follow button, I post lots of food inspo like this 🥰

Crispy Steak Sandwich with Basil Aioli & Tomato Confit
Serves 2

For the Sandwich
✨ 4 slices sourdough bread (or 1 small loaf, halved and sliced) pan fried
✨ 1 ribeye steak (about 10–12 oz), cooked or reheated
✨ ½ cup stracciatella cheese
✨ Balsamic glaze, for drizzling
✨ Salt and pepper, to taste
✨ Tomato confit (see below)
✨ basil aioli (see below)
✨ Marinated arugula (see below)

Tomato Confit
✨ 1 cup Sugar Bomb tomatoes
✨ 1 garlic clove, minced
✨ 1 small shallot, minced
✨ 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, minced
✨ Salt and pepper, to taste

In a skillet with a drizzle of olive oil, sauté tomatoes with garlic, shallots, parsley, salt and pepper until the tomatoes are soft, blistered.

Basil Aioli
✨ 1 garlic clove
✨ Pinch of salt
✨ Juice of 1 lemon
✨ ¼ cup fresh basil leaves
✨ ⅓ cup mayo

Crush the garlic clove with a pinch of salt into a paste. Add the lemon juice and let it sit for about 10 minutes to mellow the garlic. Add basil  and grind until smooth. Stir in mayo and season to taste.

Marinated Arugula Salad
✨ 1 cup arugula
✨ 1 tablespoon olive oil
✨ 1 teaspoon balsamic vinegar
✨ Grated Parmesan, to taste
✨ Salt and pepper, to taste

Toss arugula with olive oil, balsamic vinegar, a pinch of salt and pepper, and a light sprinkle of Parmesan until evenly coated.

Crispy Steak
If using leftover steak, reheat it in a skillet with butter and olive oil until edges are crispy. If using fresh steak, season simply with salt and pepper, sear in a hot pan, and let it rest before slicing thinly.

Comment TOMATO TART for links to anything seen in this video or RECIPE &  I will send you a DM! 

I shared this tomato tart last summer and so many of you made it and absolutely loved it! So here’s a reminder to make it again while heirloom tomatoes are still in season! And if you made it last year, make sure to leave me a comment letting me know!! 

Tomato Tarte with pistachio whipped feta 
✨puff pastry 
✨1 egg
✨pistachio whipped feta (recipe below)
✨tomatoes 
✨chopped pistachios 
✨salt and pepper
✨evoo
✨optional hot honey for drizzling 

1.	Preheat your oven to 400°F.
2.	Spread the puff pastry on a baking sheet.
3.	Score the pastry about an inch away from the edge to form a rectangle.
4.	Lightly press a fork throughout the inner rectangle and brush with egg wash
5.	Bake the pastry for 25-30 minutes, until fully cooked.
6.	Remove the pastry from the oven and lightly press down the center with a spoon.
7.	Spread whipped feta over the pressed pastry.
8.	Layer tomato slices on top.
9.	Add crushed pistachios, salt, and pepper.
10.	Drizzle with olive oil and hot honey 

Enjoy!

Pistachio whipped feta 
 ✨8 oz feta
✨4 oz cream cheese
✨1 oz Parmesan cheese
✨1/4 cup pistachio
✨1 small garlic clove
✨2 Tablespoons evoo
✨2 Tablespoons lemon juice (about 1 whole lemon) 
✨1 Tablespoon honey 
✨splash of milk (optional for thinner  consistency)

Blend all ingredients in a food processor. If you’re using a blender you may need to use extra milk to thin it out. I def recommend using a food processor if you have it for a less runny consistency.

Sunday Snacks – Ep. 8 Every Sunday I share snack style recipes that feel a little fancy but are super easy to make. This week we’re making pan con tomate! It’s a classic Spanish tapa made with toasted bread, garlic, fresh tomato, olive oil, and salt, super simple but so good.

🍅Comment PAN CON TOMATE for links to shop this video and RECIPE sent to your DMs! 

Here’s how I like to make mine:

Ingredients
✨Sourdough bread, sliced
✨Olive oil (for frying + drizzling)
✨1 garlic clove, peeled
✨1 extra large ripe tomatoes 
✨flaky salt, to taste
TOPPINGS:
✨castelvetrano olives
✨Capers
✨Parmigiano Reggiano (or Manchego to keep it traditional)
✨evoo + flaky salt for finishing

Instructions
1.	Pan-fry slices of sourdough in olive oil until golden and crispy on both sides.
2.	While the bread is still warm, rub it with a peeled garlic clove.
3.	Grate  your tomatoes until all that’s left is the skin, then press the mixture through a fine-mesh strainer to remove excess liquid. You want it thick, not watery.
4.	Season the tomato pulp with sea salt and a drizzle of extra-virgin olive oil.
5.	Spoon the tomato mixture generously over your garlicky toast.
6.	Top with  olives, capers, Parmigiano Reggiano (or Manchego), and finish with a touch of flaky salt and more olive oil.

Sunday Snacks – Ep. 10 Every Sunday I share snack-style recipes that feel a little fancy but are easy to recreate. This week I’m sharing my Cherry Bomb Bites, a spicy/sweet combo of marinated cherries, creamy Boursin, and crunchy pistachios on top of a crisp cucumber! These are little flavor bombs you have to make them!

Cherry Bomb Bites 
 Ingredients
✨1 English cucumber, sliced into thick rounds- make sure it’s ice cold!
✨1 package Boursin cheese 
✨1 cup fresh cherries, pitted and halved
✨1/2 Tablespoon chili crisp I used @whiteelephant_thai 
✨1 Tablespoon honey
✨2 tablespoons roasted pistachios, crushed
✨Flaky salt, to finish

Instructions
1.	In a small bowl, combine the halved cherries, chili crisp, and honey. Let them marinate while you prep everything else (about 10 min).
2.	Meanwhile, slice cucumber 
3.	Top cucumber with a generous dollop of Boursin cheese.
5.	Layer a spoonful of the marinated cherry mixture.
6.	Sprinkle flaky salt over the top and finish with crushed pistachios.

caption:
We spent most of the day driving from Istanbul to Kusadasi, so we had a super random assortment of food! 

We were really interested to see what a Turkish grocery store would be like, so we stopped at one and we were honestly so surprised! Like, they had hot food and the omelette was SO yum. 

We stopped in Bergama for the ruins (which were amazing!!), and one of the guys there recommended a restaurant called Altin Kepce. It served three main things, bergama koftesi being the main dish. Super delicious and yummy! I was a particular fan of the Kemal Pasha, which is a cheese and semolina dessert covered in tahini🤯

after a long day at the beaches, we finished our drive to Kusadasi but were so hungry so we stopped at what we thought was a gas station but it actually turned out to be a full restaurant dedicated to meat?? 

They had like a butchers part where you pick out the meat and then they grill/make it for you. The waitress was so funny, we kept trying to order in Turkish and she couldn’t stop laughing which made us start laughing and all of us just couldn’t get words out for a few minutes 😭 

regardless, I really enjoyed all the food and can’t wait to try more Turkish food! 

LMK any regional specialities I should try in Konya or Cappadoccia!

caption:
Choc Brownie Baked oats (meal prep style 😚)

Breakfast sorted for the week 🫡👩🏼‍🍳⭐️

Ingredients (for each glass bowl):
1/2 cup oats 
1/2 tsp baking powder
2 tbsp choc protein powder (using @nakedharvestsupplements as always 💁🏼‍♀️ - dc: TANISHA)
1/2 tbsp cocoa powder 
1 tbsp sweetener 
1 tbsp vanilla high protein yoghurt
1/2-3/4 cup milk**
1 square dark chocolate, roughly chopped

**depending on consistency of protein powder used

Method:
Combine all the dry ingredients into an oven proof dish. Mix in the wet ingredients. The mixture shouldn’t be too thick. Top with dark chocolate

Bake in the oven for ~15-20 minutes at 180C/350F 

Keep in the fridge & heat in the microwave before eating

I also top with @mayversfood choc hazelnut spread 🤌🏼

Enjoy T x

Banana Bread Baked Oats

My most viral baked oats recipe 😮‍💨😮‍💨

Ingredients:
1/2 cup oats
2 tbsp vanilla protein powder (I used @nakedharvestsupplements - dc: TANISHA)
1/2 tsp baking powder 
1/3 - 1/2 cup milk of choice (depending on type of protein used)
1/2 banana mashed (+ remaining 1/2 to top)

sprinkle of cinnamon (to top ~ optional)

Blend oats in a food processor to form a flour consistency. 
Combine all dry ingredients into an oven proof dish. Mix in the banana and milk. Top with sliced banana and sprinkle of cinnamon. Bake at 170C for ~15 minutes (the longer the more cakey). 

**I have also recently added in 1/2 tsp of @kizactivelife banana bread mix with @spicetub and it really takes these to the next level 😮‍💨

I topped with a choc sauce (1 square of dark choc melted + almond milk)

Enjoy T x

Chicken Teriyaki Rice Bowl

One of my favourite savoury dishes that is packed full of so much goodness, made using @blucookware - 100% toxin and PFAS free.
 
When I initially started my journey towards cooking more consciously, I focused on buying local and seasonal produce with the aim to reduce my carbon footprint and support local farmers. However, I’ve since expanded my conscious journey to go beyond just the ingredients that I select, but the cookware that I use in the kitchen too. Blu. has been my ideal choice to complete my journey towards toxin-free cooking. With Blu. cookware, I feel more confident about cooking nourishing meals without compromising on my health (or flavour). 
 
@blucookware is the perfect choice for all the conscious cooks out there who are looking to live a cleaner, more holistic lifestyle while still preserving the freshness and flavour of ingredients.

Ingredients (serves 2):
2 x chicken breast 
1 tbsp olive oil

Teryaki sauce:
3 tbsp soy sauce
3 tbsp rice vinegar/mirin
3 tbsp water
2 tbsp honey
1/4 tsp ground ginger

To serve:
rice
broccolini, steamed
spring onion, thinly sliced
sesame seeds

Method:
In a small bowl, mix together the teriyaki sauce ingredients.
Pour over chicken to fully coat.
In a saucepan, drizzle in olive oil. Remove chicken from sauce and around 3 minutes on each side
Pour sauce over and leave to thicken (2-3 minutes)
Flip chicken over so fully coated in sauce
Remove from pan and leave any excess sauce to drip off
Slice the chicken into thick pieces.
Serve on a bed of rice with a side of greens and sprinkle of sesame seeds.
Drizzle over the excess teriyaki sauce 

Enjoy T x

caption:
🍍🥩Comment STEAK SALAD for links to shop this video or RECIPE and I’ll send a DM! 

Charred Pineapple Steak Salad with Chimichurri Burrata - The combination of the chimichurri pesto with the sweet pineapple, and the charred steak is insanely good!! You have to try it!

For the Steak & Marinade
✨2 ribeye steaks(or flanks)
✨⅓ cup low-sodium soy sauce
✨Juice of 2 limes
✨juice of 1 orange
✨2 garlic cloves, minced or zested

Marinate steaks with soy sauce, lime juice, orange juice, and garlic.for at least 30 minutes. Heat a cast-iron skillet over high heat. Sear steaks to your preferred doneness. Let them rest before slicing.

For the Chimichurri Pesto
✨½ cup flat leaf parsley
✨¼ cup cilantro
✨1 garlic clove
✨ 1/2 shallot
✨¼ tsp red pepper flakes (optional)
✨2 tbsp red wine vinegar
✨¼ cup pistachios or walnuts
✨¼ cup grated Parmesan
✨⅓ cup olive oil
✨Salt, to taste
✨Juice of ½ lime

Add all ingredients to a blender or food processor and Blend until smooth but still textured. Taste and adjust salt.

For the Salad Base & Assembly
✨1 small pineapple cubed
✨2 cups arugula
✨1 ball of burrata

1. After cooking the steak, use the same skillet to cook pineapple cubes until caramelized and lightly charred.
2. Toss arugula lightly with a spoonful of chimichurri pesto and place on a plate.
3. Top with sliced steak, burrata, and charred pineapple.
4. Drizzle more chimichurri pesto over the steak and burrata.

Crispy Yellow Squash Chips (Air Fried)
Ingredients
✨1 yellow squash, thinly sliced (use a mandolin)
¼ cup flour
✨1 tbsp cornstarch
✨3–4 tbsp club soda or seltzer water (enough to make a loose batter)
✨¼ cup panko
✨2 tbsp grated Parmesan
✨¼ tsp garlic salt
✨¼ tsp Italian herbs
✨Avocado spray oil

Mix flour, cornstarch, and seltzer water into a thin batter. Combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan, garlic salt, and Italian herbs. Dip squash slices into the wet batter, coat in the breadcrumb mix, spray with avocado oil, and air fry at 400°F for 8–10 minutes, flipping halfway, until crispy and golden.

Protein Cinnamon Donuts

The perfect dessert that is ready to go in less than 20minutes!! 🍩🍩

~9.5g protein | 94 cals 

Ingredients (makes 6):
1/2 cup plain flour
1/2 cup vanilla protein - I use @nakedharvestsupplements (dc: TANISHA to save 15%)
2 tsp baking powder
2 tbsp granulated natural sweetener (or sugar alternative)
2 tsp cinnamon
pinch of nutmeg
1/3 cup high protein yoghurt
2/3 cup low fat milk

Cinnamon sugar: granulated natural sweetener (or sugar alternative) + cinnamon

Method:
Preheat oven to 170C (fan forced)
Combine all dry ingredients in a bowl
Stir in wet ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a non-stick donut tray
Bake for 10-12 minutes. Leave to cool slightly
Lightly brush with melted butter and top with cinnamon sugar

Enjoy T x

caption:
Is it possible to make $10k/month on LinkedIn?

Six months ago, I set a goal that felt insane. Go from zero followers to $10k/month, and if it worked, I would drop out and chase content creation full time. On January 1st, 2025, I started posting with nothing but consistency.

After 60 days of daily posting, I landed my first $500 brand deal. By 90 days, I reached $3k/month with 50k followers and multiple sponsors. But then growth stalled, engagement dropped, and brands started leaving.

Instead of quitting, I doubled down. I started posting 3 times a day, experimenting with new formats, and engaging relentlessly. After three more months of focused grinding, I hit 100k followers and $7k/month with brands like Lovable, Replit, and Notion.

Now I am closing in on $10k/month, proof that anyone can build a career by simply sharing their thoughts and showing up every single day on LinkedIn.

If I can do it, so can you.

caption:
🥯Comment SAVORY DONUTS for links and recipe sent to your dms! 

I made this with McKenzie-Childs on another platform to share the Rosy check collection, but I had to bring this recipe here! These are Bagels, but with a twist! I actually started making these because I love the way that donuts look, but I’m more of a savory girl and this is much more up my alley! 

I like to call these:
Savory Donuts 
✨bagels
✨1/4 cup grated Parmesan
✨Butter
✨stracciatella cheese 
✨blueberries and strawberries 
✨flaky salt 
✨balsamic glaze
✨ dried flower petals

1. Preheat the oven to 400°F
2. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
3. Spread butter on the cut side of your bagel, then place it butter-side down on top of the Parmesan.
4. Bake for about 6 minutes or until golden brown.
5. Top with stracciatella.
6. Add fresh berries.
7. Sprinkle with flaky salt and dried flower petals.
8. Drizzle with balsamic glaze and enjoy!

This will become your new favorite spring salad!  The blueberries with the candied pistachios is simply amazing!! 

Blueberry Crunch Salad:
✨ 5 oz spring mix
✨ 1 cup fresh blueberries
✨ 1/3 cup crumbled feta crumbles 
✨1/2 small red onion thinly sliced
✨1/2 a watermelon radish thinly sliced 
✨ candied pistachios (recipe below)

Poppy Seed  Dressing:
✨ 1/2 cup olive oil
✨ 1/4 cup white wine or champagne vinegar
✨ 3 Tbsp sugar 
✨ 2 tsp poppy seeds
✨ 1/4 tsp salt
✨ 1 tsp Dijon mustard
✨ 2 tsp mayo

Candied Pistachios
Ingredients:
✨ 1 cup raw shelled pistachios
✨ 2 Tbsp sugar
✨ 2 Tbsp honey
✨ Pinch of salt

Directions:
In a nonstick pan, heat sugar and honey over medium heat until bubbling. Add pistachios and stir constantly for 4–5 minutes until coated and golden. Spread on parchment and let cool completely.

To Assemble:
Layer spring mix, blueberries, feta, and cooled candied pistachios. Drizzle with dressing and serve fresh.

caption: Self love means attending a flower bouquet workshop and making yourself a pink bouquet💐✨🌷 dress from: @hurreofficial

Carrot Cake Baked Oats

I am shocked that it has taken me this long to try this combo. Honestly so underrated 🤤

Meal Prep Carrot Cake Baked Oats
Ingredients (serves 3):
2 cups oats
2 small bananas
2 cups milk
1/2 cup vanilla protein powder
1.5 tsp baking powder
3 tbsp sugar free maple syrup 
2 tsp cinnamon 
1/3 cup finely shredded carrot

Method:
Preheat oven to 180C
In a @vitamix_aunz processor (or regular blender), add in all ingredients (except the carrot). Blend on speed 5 for ~40 seconds or until smooth.

Distribute mixture evenly between 3 oven proof containers. Distribute the carrot and mix in. 

Bake for 20-25 minutes (bake time will depend on the texture you prefer - longer will make it more cake like)

Enjoy T x

caption:
Spicy Vodka Pasta 🌶️🌶️

Vodka pasta has been all over my feed again recently so take this as your sign to add it to your list this week!!

Ingredients (serves 2):
1 tbsp olive oil
1 small onion, finely diced
2 garlic cloves, minced
1 tsp chilli flakes
1/3 cup tomato paste
1/2 cup thickened cooking cream
1 tbsp vodka
200g dry rigatoni
to serve - basil, extra chilli flakes, Parmesan cheese 

Method:
Cook pasta per packet instructions.

In a pan, heat the olive oil on a medium heat. Add in the onion and cook until soft and transulscent (around 4 mins). 
Add in the garlic, chilli flakes, and tomato paste. Cook until the colour deepens.
Stir through the vodka and cook for 3 minutes until completely evaporated. 
Add in the cream and stir on a low heat until fully combined.
Add in a pinch of salt.

Once the sauce is cooked take off the heat and add in the pasta. Lightly toss to combine.

3 steps to a cinematic masterpiece 👇🏻

1. Lighting 🔆 lighting makes up 80% of the shot, so always prioritise this. 

2. Colour grade 🎨 the extra special sauce to add depth and feeling to the shot. 

3. Colour separation 🟩🟨🟥 how you arrange colours and include contrasting vibrant colours, can do SO much more than you might think to make a shot interesting.

↓ How to change your self-image ↓

Comment ‘’Self-Esteem’’ to get my free self-esteem guide ❤️

When you change your self-image, you change your life.

My clients have gone from socially anxious, to feeling calm & confident by doing this exact practice & today I am giving it away for free.

So SAVE it for later ❤️

1. Get clear on what negative beliefs you currently carry about yourself.

2. Realise that your mind always tries to proof the things it already beliefs. So you don’t see a reflection of reality, you see a reflection of your self-image in your outside world.

3. Reframe the negative beliefs into positive ones.

4. Look for evidence of these new beliefs every day. You self-image (and subconscious mind) can only be rewired through repetition.

5. Stop the narrative of the negative self-image, when it comes up.

This is just 1 step of my Reframe Method, the Method that helped my clients finally overcome their social anxiety and feel confident in who they are.

Sourdough is a gut-friendly and naturally fermented bread, but the real transformation happens when we start to use freshly-milled flour in our dough!

Most store-bought flour has gone through heavy processing. In the process, the bran and germ, where most of the vitamins, minerals, healthy oils, and fiber live, are STRIPPED AWAY to extend its shelf life. This means we are baking with flour that’s been sitting for months, lacking both flavor and nutrition 😌

I have started milling my own flour at home using the MOCKMILL Electric Grain Mill so that I can bake with flour that is 100% alive — rich in B vitamins, antioxidants, essential fatty acids, and full of depth and aroma that are all absent in store-bought flours. The difference in flavor is instantly noticeable, and your body will thank you for the extra nutrition 💪💪

🌟 ᴇxᴄʟᴜsɪᴠᴇ ᴅɪsᴄᴏᴜɴᴛ ʟɪɴᴋ ɪɴ ᴍʏ ʙɪᴏ 

ɢᴇᴛ ᴀɴ ᴇxᴄʟᴜsɪᴠᴇ 𝟻% ᴏғғ ᴡɪᴛʜ ᴍʏ ᴄᴏᴅᴇ “sʜᴇʙᴀᴋᴇsᴏᴜʀᴅᴏᴜɢʜ”

🌟 𝑅𝑒𝑐𝑖𝑝𝑒 𝑐𝑎𝑛 𝑏𝑒 𝑓𝑜𝑢𝑛𝑑 𝑖𝑛 𝑡ℎ𝑒 𝑐𝑜𝑚𝑚𝑒𝑛𝑡 𝑠𝑒𝑐𝑡𝑖𝑜𝑛 

WHY MILL YOUR OWN FLOUR ?

✅ FRESHNESS FOR GREATER FLAVOUR

Oils in whole grains oxidize quickly after milling, leading to bland or bitter flavour. Milling at home ensures freshness and bold flavor.

✅ NUTRITIONAL VALUE

Whole grain flour includes all parts of the grain:

⭐️ Bran (fiber)

⭐️ Germ (vitamins, minerals, healthy fats)

⭐️ Endosperm (carbohydrates and protein)

In most store-bought flours, the bran and germ are stripped away to improve shelf life—along with much of the nutrition. Fresh flour retains essential nutrients, enzymes, and fiber.

✅ CUSTOMISATION 

Control the texture and type and create your own favourite flour mix.

I’m using the Mockmill Lino 100 Grain Miller from @grainlovers.official .  It is an electric mill that’s fast, efficient and easy to clean!

The secret of your future is hidden in your daily routines 🌟

#routine #morningroutine #samedaydifferentchoices #youvsyou #habits

getting myself out of a slump!! 🤍

I never want to come on here and bring a negative energy, but I also never want to hide my struggles because I know how much it can help to see others going through it when you are too 💭 

It’s so easy to get caught up in sharing the highlights on social media, and while I am so incredibly grateful for the life I live and truely do pinch myself every single day, it’s totally normal to have days, weeks or even months that just feel…. bleh!! 🥺

A few things that I love to do when I’m feeling like this 
🌟 stay in routine as much as possible // this includes waking up early! It doesn’t have to be 5:00am, but sleeping in until 10am most likely isn’t going to help you feel any better (even though it sounds very tempting sometimes) 
🌟 move your body // you are probably sick of hearing people say this, but movement truely is medicine. Movement will release endorphins & boost your mood - so get outside for a run/ walk, book a Pilates class with a friend or go solo, whatever makes you feel good!! 
🌟 take care of yourself, inside & out // fuel your body with nourishing food, drink plenty of water, put on a cute outfit, journal your thoughts, and do the little things that make you feel like you again!! 

And most importantly, be gentle with yourself. It’s okay to have slower days, to feel off, or to not tick every box. Nothing blooms all year long 🌸

As an Indian, my parents always taught me that “friends will never be there for you like family will” and I spent the first 18 years of my life being told not to value friendships and platonic closeness. 

Nothing was ever more important than studies, secrets should stay within the family, and you can have a social life after you’re married.

But oh how they’ve been proved wrong. My friends are some of the dearest things in my life - and they’ve been there for me in ways my family have never. And I can say without a doubt that they know me, the real me, better than my parents.

Blood may be thicker than water; but isn’t water what keeps you living? 🌊🤍

LESSON NO. 6/23 ✧ how to filter advice 
-
asking for advice is something we all do. we ask for advice when we need help making big decisions, or when we’re curious how others would approach similar situations in our lives. 
-
when you go to interpret that advice, I learned this year that it’s always important to consider the context or circumstances of the person giving you the advice. 
-
a solid example might be if you’re debating on quitting your job. a friend might suggest you just quit, but they have no clue what your financial situation is and theirs might look different. it’s always good to ask for advice but to also consider how heavily you want to weigh that advice :) you know yourself best so have faith in yourself 
-
how do you filter out advice? 
-

caption:
Stay in the present, stay consistent, & stay balanced 

#motivationalquotesdaily #inspirationalquotesdaily #curlyhairgrowth #selfgrowth #mindset

I saw someone be really transparent with their audience… so I thought I’d give it a try.

1.	I’ve been chasing a position at my bank for four years. I’ve worked there since I was a freshman in college — 18 years old, balancing classes while working full-time. Now, five years later, I’m one of the top salespeople in my region. I’ve built relationships, hit my numbers, and earned a reputation for results. This interview should feel like the moment I’ve been waiting for… yet instead of pride, I find myself wondering if I truly deserve it — how it’s possible to work so hard, check all the boxes, and still feel like I’m not enough.

	2.	Before 23, I started five businesses — all failed. Not from lack of passion, but from lack of resources, guidance, and hands-on learning. Two years ago, I came up with the idea for my agency, but didn’t take action until six months ago. Since then, I’ve signed clients, built momentum, and watched my vision take shape — even if it feels slow. My head is full of ideas, my notes app overflowing with plans, but between my job, my business, and my personal life, finding the time to execute them feels impossible.
	
3.	Content creation is a passion, but it’s the first thing I push aside when life gets hectic. My 9–5, agency, nonprofit, and family take most of my hours. Sleep is the sacrifice, and burnout follows. I stop going to the gym. My confidence dips. Even with quick Pilates sessions or sorority dance practice, I still feel behind.
	
4.	On Instagram, it might look like I’m living my best life — traveling, creating, posting good vibes. But behind the scenes, I’m juggling responsibilities, running on low energy, and torn between sharing my story and protecting my privacy.
	
5.	Recently, I signed with a talent agency for brand deals, trips, and collabs. At the same time, I’m preparing for my “dream” bank interview — but part of me wonders if I should go all in on my business and content. It’s a tug-of-war between stability and freedom. I don’t know exactly where this road is leading, but I know this: whatever God’s plan is, I trust it. And it will all work out. 🤍

Okay… I might’ve underestimated a few things 😅

And that’s not even counting my trisuit and wetsuit (+€1000) 😬

Here’s a quick breakdown of what I’ve spent for my first Ironman — just to give you an idea:

Bike 🚲

- TT bike: €5000
- Power meter: €300
- Bike computer: €400
- Hydration system + bottle cages: €500
- Maintenance: €400
- Cycling shoes: €250
- Aero helmet: €500
- Indoor trainer: €500
- Road bike: €500

Run & swim 
- 3 pairs of shoes: €500
- Goggles: €50
- Accessories: €50
- Wetsuit: €400

Other costs
- Race entry: €900
- Transport: €500
- Accommodation: €500
- Trisuit: €200

this is MY average and doesn’t have to be yours. Everything is doable on a budget, but for me it’s something I’m probably doing for the next few years, so I’m oke with spending some money on it. Healthy hobbies cost money ;)

#marathon #ironman #running #hybridathlete #triathlete #triatlon

I don’t want to give a false picture. Besides all the nice things I share on Instagram, I’m just a normal guy from a small town. I try to go through life with a smile, but I also have my tough moments. I feel jealous sometimes, I feel sad, and some days, I just don’t want to do anything. 

Still, I always try to make the best of my days, see the good side, and enjoy every moment on this floating rock. I’m grateful that my family is healthy and that I have a home. I’m also really thankful for your support and excited to see what the future brings. 

Love, 
Jens

High Protein Meal Prep McGriddles 🔥
44g Protein 💪🏼

Comment “cookbook” & I’ll send you all the details for my recipe eBooks with over 230 healthy high protein recipes👨🏻‍🍳📚

(Macros: Per Serving - 6 Total)
443 Calories
22gC | 16gF | 44gP

Ingredients: 
250g Plain All Purpose Flour (Vetta Smart Plain Flour - can be substituted for self raising flour)
1 Tsp Baking Powder
1 Tsp Cinnamon
35g Zero Calorie Sweetener (Natvia Natural Sweetener)
1 Egg
335ml Low Fat Milk
Sugar Free Maple Syrup
600g Extra Lean Beef Mince
1 Tsp Salt, 1 Tsp Onion Powder, 1 Tsp Garlic Powder, 1/2 Tsp Sage, 1/2 Tsp Thyme
6 Eggs, 1 Tsp Sat & 100g Blended Cottage Cheese
6 Slices Cheddar Cheese (Dairyworks Natural Cheddar Cheese)

Instructions: 
1. In a bowl add all purpose flour, baking powder, cinnamon, zero calorie sweetener & mix well.
2. Add an egg, low fat milk & mix well until you have a thick pancake batter (add more milk if needed)
3. Spray a pan with light cooking oil spray, evenly distribute the batter into two seperate silicone egg rings with some a drizzle of sugar free maple syrup on top. Place a lid on the pan & cook for 3 - 5 minutes on medium heat or until you see bubbles at the top then flip & cook again. Repeat this process until you have 12 pancakes.
4. In a seperate bowl add extra lean beef mince with the seasonings, mix well & form 6 equal balls.
5. To a pan add the mince ball, flatten & cook on medium - high heat for 2 minutes on each side.
6. In a seperate bowl mix together 6 eggs with blended cottage cheese (this step boosts the protein & also makes the eggs fluffier)
7. To a small pan add a thin layer of the egg mixture, once it’s cooked fold the edges towards the middle to create an egg pocket. Repeat the process to make 6 egg pockets in total.
8. Assemble each McGriddle by adding a slice of cheddar cheese on one pancake followed by a mince patty, one egg pocket & another pancake on top.

High Protein Korean Fried Chicken Mac & Cheese 🍗🧀
65g Protein Meal Prep 💪🏼

Comment “cookbook” & I’ll send you all the details for my recipe eBooks with over 230 healthy high protein recipes👨🏻‍🍳📚

Ingredients: 
700g Diced Skinless & Boneless Chicken Breast (raw weight)
1 Egg
10g Minced Garlic
10g Minced Ginger
1/2 Tsp White Pepper
1 Tsp Salt
150g Potato Starch (not all of this gets used - approximately 40g sticks to the chicken in total)
Light Cooking Oil Spray (FryLight)

Korean Glaze:
90ml Salt Reduced Soy Sauce & 90ml Water
20g Natural Sweetener (Natvia Natural Brown Sweetener)
10g Minced Garlic
10g Minced Ginger
2 - 3 Tsp Tsp Gochujang Chilli Paste 
1 Tsp Potato Starch or Corn Starch Mixed With Water
1 Tsp Chilli Flakes

Mac & Cheese:
340ml Fat Free Evaporated Milk (Carnation Light & Creamy)
1 Tsp Smoked Paprika & 1 Tsp Chicken Stock Powder (Vegeta Salt Reduced Chicken Stock Powder)
80g Light Cream Cheese
100g Light Grated Cheddar Cheese (Dairyworks Natural Cheddar Cheese)
320g Macaroni/Elbow Pasta (dry weight)

IMPORTANT NOTES:
When reheating add a drop of milk in the mac & cheese beforehand, this will make it creamy again.
Reheat the chicken with the mac & cheese or preferably separately in the air fryer / oven for a few minutes for maximum crispiness.

High Protein Cheesy Chicken Parm Rolls 🍗🌯
Easy 40g Protein Meal Prep! 🔥

Don’t forget to check out my recipe eBooks with over 230 easy, high protein recipes like this one 👨🏻‍🍳📖

(Macros: Per Roll - 10 Total)
363 Calories
23.4gC | 10.3gF | 40.8gP

Ingredients: 
1KG Boneless & Skinless Chicken Breast (slice in half & flatten)
1 Tsp Salt, 1 Tsp Italian Herb Seasoning, 1 Tsp Garlic Powder, 1 Tsp Onion Powder, 1 Tsp Smoked Paprika
2 Eggs (whisked)
150g Plain Flour (not all of this gets used - approximately 3g sticks to each chicken breast)
150g Panko/Italian Breadcrumbs (add a dash of the same seasonings used above)
Light Cooking Oil Spray
10 Warm Tortillas (Woolworths Soft White Wraps)
35g Marinara/Pizza Sauce (per roll)
35g Blended Low Fat Cottage Cheese (per roll)
30g Grated Light Mozzarella Cheese (per roll)
5g Grated Parmesan Cheese (per roll)
Dried Parsley
Optional Toppings: Parsley Flakes & Parmesan Cheese

Important Notes:
- To save even more time you can completely skip the coating step for the crispy chicken & simply season the chicken & cook it on a pan/air fryer to make grilled chicken. 
- Not all the flour & breadcrumbs get used - to accurately calculate the macros weigh the chicken before & after you dip it in the flour/breadcrumbs. This will tell you exactly how much was used & stuck to the chicken in total

Life doesn’t always work out the way we want it to, and sometimes we don’t understand why things happen the way they do and that’s okay.

In 2023, we experienced a quiet loss, our first pregnancy ended a day before our first scan. It was one of the most heartbreaking things I’ve ever gone through, and it took me a long time to begin healing. But as time passed, I started to realise the importance of patience and the strength that comes from fully trusting Allah’s plan.

To all my mamas who have gone through something similar you’re in my prayers. I see you, I feel you, and I truly hope your heart is healing. 🤍

This time, Alhamdulilah, Allah has blessed us with another gift. Me and my husband found out at the same time, surrounded by our family. We didn’t document much of our initial reactions, and the memories we did capture from that moment I’ve chosen to keep for myself ❤️

Allah’s plans are always greater than what we could ever imagine and this journey feels even more meaningful because of what came before it. Please do keep us in your duas 🤍🤍

How to Lock In to Your Purpose & Succeed 🚀

🔑 Step 1 – Power ON the Right Habits
✔ Discipline – Show up every day, even when you don’t feel like it.
✔ Lock In – Remove distractions and focus on one main goal.
✔ Sacrifice – Trade short-term comfort for long-term wins.

🛑 Step 2 – Power OFF the Roadblocks
❌ Excuses – Stop telling yourself “I’ll start tomorrow.”
❌ Lack of Effort – Dreams need action, not just ideas.

💭 Step 3 – Find Your Purpose
	•	Ask yourself: What excites me? What problems do I want to solve? Who do I want to help?
	•	Look at your skills, passions, and life experiences — your purpose is often where they overlap.
	•	Test and try things until one lights a fire in you.

⚖ Step 4 – Create Balance
Work your 9–5 to fund your present.
Work your 5–9 to build your future.

💡 Truth: Purpose isn’t found in one big moment — it’s built in the small, consistent steps you take daily.

📌 Start today. Turn ON what serves you. Turn OFF what’s holding you back. That’s how you log in and level up.

Freshly milled flour is a complete game changer for flavor, nutrition, and aroma! It connects us to the process of breadmaking in a deeply satisfying and meaningful way, adding richness and complexity that store-bought flour cannot replicate. 

In most store-bought flours, the bran and germ are stripped away to improve shelf life, along with much of the nutrition. 

Freshly-milled whole grain flour includes all parts of the grain:

✅ Bran (fiber)

✅ Germ (vitamins, minerals, healthy fats)

✅ Endosperm (carbohydrates and protein)

I’m using the Mockmill Lino 100 from @grainlovers.official . It is the perfect size and capacity for me, serving all my needs as a regular homebaker! It features a sturdy and reliable motor with strong milling power that produces a consistently fine-grain flour perfect for making sourdough! Most importantly it is so easy to operate and clean up!

Milling your own flour opens the door to creative, nutritious, and flavorful baking. It’s a small effort with a big payoff—transforming even a simple loaf of bread into something deeply personal and delicious!

Whether you bake once a week or every day, fresh flour will elevate your craft and deepen your connection to the grain. 

Are you ready to join me to transform your sourdough journey with the Mockmill grain miller as we experiment with new recipes using freshly-milled flour?

Bold, smoky, and bursting with flavor — this smoked paprika sourdough is the MAIN CHARACTER in my sourdough world!

Swirled with vibrant homemade red pesto and generously layered with rich smoked cheddar, every slice delivers a perfect balance of warmth, depth, and tang 😋

This is my first time making red pesto at home and it was simply AMAZING! 🤤

Whether toasted for breakfast or paired with soup, this loaf brings comfort with a kick. Crafted with care and packed with personality, it’s not just bread. It’s a flavor-packed experience that is worth every effort to make it yourself at home!

💫 I’m using the KneadAce All-in-One Sourdough Kit which includes a 32oz sourdough jar, 1 round & 1 oval cotton rope banetton baskets, and a magnetic bread lame for effortless and precise scoring!

Don’t miss out, please find the exclusive discount links in my Bio!

RECIPE

Main Dough -

320g Bread Flour

80g Semolina Flour

12g Smoked Paprika 

290g Water

80g Levain

6g Salt

Inclusions -

50g Homemade Red Pesto

50g Smoked Cheddar (cut into cubes)

BAKING INSTRUCTIONS 

➡️ Load the dough into the preheated oven and bake at 250 C with steam for 20min (for best results, use a preheated baking steel)

Open the oven door and remove the steam tray 

➡️ Lower the temperature to 215C and continue to bake for another 15-20 min

This bread itself is the perfect dessert loaf, sweet and tangy and it also pairs beautifully with savory toppings, imagine sharp cheddar, crispy bacon, or a smear of whipped goat cheese, for that unbeatable sweet-and-salty combo! It can be enjoyed as a simple breakfast with a slather of salty butter or as a satisfying afternoon treat!

A beautiful blend of comfort, crunch, and slow-fermented flavor, let the aroma fill your kitchen and your soul 🍎😍

Optimal steam and high heat using the Brod & Taylor bread steel and baking shell ensures that the sourdough crust is crisp and golden, while the inside stays tender with pockets of apple pie filling and crumble in every bite!

It is so light and fragrant! One bite, and I promise you’ll be hooked!

Many of you would be curious about how saffron tastes in bread, and I was too! Saffron has a complex flavor profile having both sweet and earthy notes, with hints of floral and honey, so I decided to pair it with dried rose petals and honeycomb!

The warm golden colour from saffron gives it a cheerful look, while delicate rose petals and bits of honeycomb create a gentle sweetness and floral depth. Truly one-of-a-kind, this bread is as stunning as it is delicious!

Behold my latest creation : the Royal Crown Brioche Loaf, made especially for you, my Kings and Queens! 👸🫅

This golden beauty is made with a sweet stiff starter, giving it an ultra-shreddy, soft and yet airy texture you’ll fall in love with! Enriched with luscious French 🧈 and 🥚 , it’s indulgent on its own or perfect for next-level French toast.

No starter? No problem! I’ve got an instant yeast version that’s just as divine. Whether you’re baking for brunch or simply to treat yourself, this loaf brings bakery-level luxury right to your kitchen.

Enriched doughs, especially those made with sourdough starter, take their time to proof. That is the reason why I rely on my Brod & Taylor proofer to keep things warm and ensure the consistency of the dough. It’s undoubtedly the game-changer in bread-making for perfect results everytime!

💫 Please find the link in my Bio for more information on the proofer 🤗

Bread Flour 600g

Milk 230g

Instant Yeast 5g

2 eggs

Sugar 80g

Salt 7g

Butter 70g

Do you enjoy the sensory pleasure and tactile feel of popping bubble wrap? Well, me too! 🙌

These mini sourdough brioche buns bake together into a soft, puffy sheet that looks just like bubble wrap! 🫧🫧

Light, airy, and delightfully cushy, each bun can be gently “popped” and springs right back—just like the real thing, only better because you can eat it! Perfect on their own as pull-apart buns, or use four minis to create a fun and quirky hamburger bun—ready to be filled with your favourite ingredients 🍔

Whether you’re snacking, sandwiching, or just playing with your food (guilty!), these bubble-wrap buns would certainly bring joy to your table!

Sourdough has never been this playful—or this irresistible! 🤩🤗

THE SERIES CREATION HANDBOOK IS FINALLY HEREEEEE <3 

for the past few months I’ve been working on a guide for how to create your own shortform series- if you’ve been following along my journey you’ll know that series-based content has really pushed me creatively over the past 2 years 

after many DMs & questions about creating content i finally decided to make a guide but this project quickly grew beyond a guide into a full on handbook :) 

so today it’s FINALLY here after many late nights, back & forth decisions, & a bit of imposter syndrome 

the handbook covers everything from ideation to getting your series out there (i breakdown how to pick an idea, my series structure, script, how I think of visual identity/style when planning my series, & even touch on overcoming roadblocks) 

the handbook automatically comes with a notion template & can be purchased using the link in my bio (also there’s currently early bird pricing for launch week) <3 

thank you for everything & all your support, I can’t wait to see how this helps you on your journey next 🙏

LESSON 23/24 ⟢ the beauty of series-based content 

last year I experimented with creating different shortform series after my 23 lessons from 2023 series blew up at the end of 2023. this way of making videos has been my favourite in terms of staying organized, consistent, & just being able to try new things without getting lost in too many unknowns. 

the advice I always have for new creatives is to try making your own series :) it doesn’t have to necessarily be about lessons but it can be applied to any theme or goal in your life as long as it reflects you / something you care for

as you may know I recently launched a handbook (the not-guide-guide) on how to make your own shortform series & it can be found in the link in my bio! currently early bird pricing is still live to make the guide as accessible as possible but early bird pricing ends on Monday April 21st at 9am EST

caption:
Yangnyeom Gyejang
5 frozen blue crabs (thawed and quartered)
⅓ cup soju (or white wine)
⅓ cup soy sauce
⅓ cup gochugaru (Korean chili powder)
2 tbsp fish sauce
2 tbsp rice malt syrup (or corn syrup)
2 tbsp green plum extract (or sugar)
¼ asian pear
½ onion
1 tbsp ginger
¼ cup garlic

Instructions
1. Prepare the Crabs
Thaw the Crabs: If the crabs are frozen, let them thaw in the refrigerator overnight or in cold water for a couple of hours.
Clean the Crabs: Remove the top shell, gills, and intestines. Rinse thoroughly under cold water. Use kitchen shears to cut the crabs into manageable pieces (e.g., halves or quarters).
2. Pre-Marinate the Crabs
Place the cleaned crabs in a large bowl.
Pour ⅓ cup of soju (or white wine) over the crabs. Toss gently to coat.
Let them sit for about 15 minutes to reduce any fishy odor. Drain and set aside.
3. Make the Spicy Marinade
In a blender or food processor, combine:
* ��¼ Asian pear
* ��½ onion
* ��1 tbsp ginger
* ��¼ cup garlic
Blend until smooth.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the blended mixture with:
* ��⅓ cup soy sauce
* ��⅓ cup gochugaru
* ��2 tbsp fish sauce
* ��2 tbsp rice malt syrup (or corn syrup)
* ��2 tsp green plum extract (or sugar)

Mix thoroughly to form a thick, well-balanced marinade.
4. Marinate the Crabs
Add the crabs to the marinade, ensuring each piece is coated thoroughly.
Transfer the crabs and marinade to an airtight container. Press the crabs gently to ensure they are fully submerged in the sauce.
5. Refrigerate
* Let the crabs marinate in the refrigerator for at least 12 hours, but for best flavor, marinate for 24-48 hours.

my advice for aspiring content creators 

1) find your niche
don’t chase what’s viral, do what feels true to you.
if it’s not something you genuinely care about most likely your shit will stink.
you can’t create something that’s for everyone; no matter how small, if it’s something that you jam with, there’s gonna be other people who’s interested as well. 
start small first then branch.

2) dont quit your job unless…
don’t quit what you’re doing now cold turkey to chase the unknown.
for almost a whole year into doing my content I still had a part-time job teaching english that paid my bills.
i made a promise to myself that once what i was making from content was more than what i made, that i would quit. 
(also u dont have to! some of the happiest creators i know have a full time job + do creating on the side as a hobby) set a goal on when to exit when the time is ripe, but don’t be rash. 
time away from making videos allows for room to treasure the process, instead of blaming the results aren’t instantaneous. 

3) quality comes with quantity 
perfectionism is what keeps you from posting.
no matter what, your first video is going to be shit 
but you’re not going to get any better by only thinking and not doing.
develop your own style and know-hows through trial and error
and remember, who cares if it’s cringe if it’s something you care about? ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

Almost one year ago I returned to social media with a genuine passion. I found my message & I committed to it, and somehow I’m now Shortlisted to receive an award from @itv @bcreatoruk for Rising Star of the Year. 

I truly am just an average girl. Daughter of immigrants, eldest by 7 years, grew up in an incredibly financially unstable home and raised in a Christian Orthodox community. 

Every step i took as I grew up was riddled with doubt & guilt and somewhere along the way I made my peace with the feeling. It’s no longer a sign that I’m doing the wrong thing but that I’m doing the right thing.

And somewhere along the way I found people that understand me. You guys. I’m so grateful for everything I’ve been given, everything I’ve worked for, and everything I’m yet to receive 🤍

Whilst it is an honour to just be nominated & shortlisted, I’d love it if you could all show some support and cast your votes for me 🥹❤️

in OVERLOOKED, we’re diving into the stories of the women in STEM who changed science, tech and medicine… but never got the credit they deserved.

we’re talking about the women who discovered, built, solved, and innovated, while their male colleagues got the awards and the footnotes in history books.

you’ve heard of WiFi, but have you heard of the Hollywood actress who helped invent the tech behind it? what about the scientist who proved the universe isn’t symmetrical, but didn’t get the Nobel? or the one whose data cracked the structure of DNA… and got written out of the story?

they laid the foundations and then, too often, they were erased.

this season, we’re putting them BACK in the spotlight. 🌟

caption:
Healthy High Protein Raising Cane’s🍗🍟
140g Protein! 💪🏼

Comment “cookbook” & i’ll send you the details for my eBooks with over 230 easy & healthy recipes like this one! 👨🏻‍🍳📚

(Macros: 3 Tenders, Fries & 45g Cane’s Sauce)
964 Calories
75gC | 30gF | 140gP

Compared to the fast food version that has 1,250 calories & only 61g of protein!

Ingredients: (Chicken)
1.1KG Boneless & Skinless Chicken Breast (butterfly & cut into 6 thin strips - macros are calculated for a 3 tender serve as shown in the video, the rest are perfect for leftovers)
Season Chicken With: 1 Tsp Smoked Paprika, 1/2 Tsp Cayenne Pepper, 1/2 Tsp Black Pepper, 1 Tsp Salt, 1 Tsp Garlic Powder
100g Potato Starch
200g Plain Flour
Season Flour Mixture With Same Seasonings As Above
1 Cup Sparkling or Soda Water
Light Cooking Oil Spray

Ingredients: (Raising Cane’s Sauce)
350g Light Mayonnaise (Heinz Light Mayonnaise)
170 Low Sugar Ketchup (Heinz 50% Less Added Sugar Ketchup)
45g Worcestershire Sauce
1 Tsp Garlic Powder
1.5 Tsp Salt
1/2 Tsp Onion Powder
1 Tsp Black Pepper

Mix everything together and pop it in the fridge to thicken.
This makes 13 servings each around 45g and only 57 calories per serve compared to the original which is nearly 200 calories for the same amount. 

Ingredients: (Fries)
400g Carisma Potatoes
1 Tsp Salt
1 Tsp Smoked Paprika
Light Cooking Oil Spray (FryLight)

IMPORTANT NOTES:
- The ingredients listed above will make 6 chicken tenders, but the macros provided are based on a 3 tender serving (plus fries & 45g sauce). I like to make extra so there’s leftovers for the next day but feel free to adjust to suit your meal plan & use half of the flour if you’re planning to just make 3 tenders.
- When coating the chicken, make sure to press the flour firmly into each strip so it sticks properly. After placing the tenders on your tray or in the air fryer, spray the chicken evenly with light cooking oil spray & make sure there are no dry or white flour patches left ,this step is key for that golden & crunchy finish.

Healthy Low Calorie BBQ Potato Chips! 🔥
Only 248 Calories!

Comment “Cookbook” & i’ll send you the details for my recipe eBooks with 230+ easy & healthy recipes like this one! 👨🏻‍🍳📚

(Macros: Total - Entire Plate)
248 Calories
52gC | 2gF | 13gP

Ingredients:
500g Peeled & Thinly Sliced Potatoes (use mandolin or knife - thinner slices result in crisper texture) 
Bowl Of Water + Ice (combine cold water + ice in a big bowl & soak, this helps remove extra starch from the potatoes to make them crunchier)
Olive Oil Spray (FryLight - or avocado oil spray) 

BBQ Seasoning Mix:
1 Tsp Brown Sugar Stevia (Natvia Gold Natural Sweetener)
1.5 Tsp Salt
1.5 Tsp Smoked Paprika
1 Tsp Garlic Powder
1 Tsp Onion Powder
1/2 Tsp Chilli Powder
 
IMPORTANT NOTES:
* This recipe uses Carisma potatoes, which are naturally lower in carbs (around 25 percent less than standard potatoes) so they help cut back on calories. That said, any potato variety like russet or sweet potato will work just as well.
* For best results, slice the potatoes super thin using a mandolin or sharp knife. The thinner the slices, the crispier they’ll turn out.

COOKING TIMES:
Air Fry = 200°C/400°F | 10 - 15 Min (flip & spray oil halfway)
Oven Bake = 200°C/400°F | 15 - 25 Min (flip & spray oil halfway)
Microwave = 8 - 12 Min (place slices on a oven safe dish with baking paper, flip & spray halfway)

Healthy Hot Honey Buffalo Chicken Tenders🍗🔥
Crunchy, High Protein & Low Calorie 💪🏼

Comment “cookbook” & i’ll send you the details for my eBooks with over 230 easy & healthy recipes like this one! 👨🏻‍🍳📚

(Macros: Per Tender - 8 Total)
233 Calories
16.5gC | 3gF | 35gP

Ingredients:
1.2KG Boneless & Skinless Chicken Breast (butterfly & slice into 8 strips)
1 Tsp Salt, 1 Tsp Hot Paprika, 1 Tsp Onion & Garlic Powder, 1/2 Tsp Chilli Powder, 1/2 Tsp Cayenne Pepper, 1/2 Tsp Oregano
200g Plain All Purpose Flour (not all of this gets used - approximately 10g - 20g sticks to the chicken per tender)
135g Potato Starch (not all of this gets used - approximately 5g - 10g sticks to chicken per tender)
Flour Seasonings (same seasonings used above)
1 Cup Soda Water/Sparkling Water
85ml Buffalo Sauce (Franks Redhot Buffalo Sauce)
40g Honey

IMPORTANT NOTES:
While air frying, make sure to check the chicken every few minutes. If you notice any dry or patchy white flour spots on the surface, give those areas another light spray of cooking oil.
This step is crucial for achieving that golden, crispy coating especially when using a flour based crust. If you skip this the coating can end up looking dry or uneven instead of crunchy and golden like traditional fried chicken.

Golden, soft, and naturally leavened, this Sourdough Ramazan Pidesi blends the deep flavor of long fermentation with the traditional look and feel of Turkish bakery bread. 

Characterised by its iconic diamond pattern and sesame crust, this version brings a rustic sourdough touch to a timeless favorite. With a pillowy interior and a beautifully crisp crust, it’s perfect served warm with cheeses, olives, or dips.

A celebration of both heritage and craft, this pide is as beautiful on the table as it is delicious to share.

RECIPE

350 g bread flour
70 g active sourdough starter
110g water
110g milk
7 g salt
15g olive oil

Bake at 250C for 10 min and 180C for 5 min

These easy sourdough seeded breakfast buns come together with minimal effort—just mix everything in one bowl, fold the dough three times, and pop it into the fridge overnight. No complicated steps, no stress!

The next morning, simply divide, roll in your favorite seeds, proof, and bake! 

You’ll be rewarded with wholesome, crusty buns that are soft and chewy on the inside, packed with flavor and texture, simply by doing nothing much and letting time take over 👍. 

Perfect for breakfast, but honestly, just as good any time of the day. Once you try them, they’ll be on repeat in your kitchen. Simple, nourishing, and so satisfying!

We ran out of sourdough bread at home and I made this quick and easy 30% whole-wheat flat sandwich bread. It turned out excellent and it’s too good not to share! 😋

This thin sandwich bread is everything you want in a bread—crisp on the outside, soft and fluffy inside 🥰 It is packed with a rich, nutty flavour with a satisfying chew. This whole-wheat bread is full of fibre and flavour, and honestly one of the best breads I’ve ever made!

Whether you’re layering it with your favourite fillings or enjoying it plain, it makes the perfect base for any sandwich. 

Today I slathered the bread with pistachio pesto and enjoyed it with prosciutto and creamy burrata 🤩🤗 It tasted INCREDIBLE! 🤤

And the best part? It’s an incredibly easy recipe that even beginners can nail!

Golden, sesame-crusted, and delightfully chewy, this sourdough Turkish simit is the perfect fusion of tradition and slow fermentation. Traditionally sold by street vendors, the Simit bagel is crisp on the outside, soft inside, and often enjoyed with tea, cheese, or olives.

My sourdough version brings a deliciously modern twist — it’s super fluffy, unbelievably chewy, and packed with deep, complex flavor from the long overnight fermentation. These braided golden rings are encrusted with roasted sesame seeds that add the perfect crunch to every bite.

Whether enjoyed plain, with cheese, alongside olives or just butter and jam, the simit is a comforting everyday staple with a satisfying crunch in every bite.

This is one of the best breads I’ve ever made… and one you’ll want to bake again and again!

RECIPE

400g Flour
120g Water
100g Milk
80g Levain
15g Sugar
8g Salt
15g Oil

Eat your Squid 🦑 Ink Pasta in bread form!

This gastronomic sourdough is inspired by the bold flavors of squid ink pasta, made with squid ink powder and 20% semolina flour to mimic its signature taste and texture.

The loaf is loaded with savoury inclusions of my homemade sun-dried tomatoes and black pepper smoked cheese, creating an irresistible umami-rich bread that teases the senses and leaves you craving more! Smoky, salty, tangy, and deeply flavourful—this bread is anything but ordinary. One bite, and you’ll understand that it tastes as good as it looks! I love how the smoked cheese melted and created a vibrant contrast to the dark-themed sourdough! 🤩

Perfect on its own or as the base for an elevated 🥪 , this successful sourdough combo yet reminds me again why I’m in ❤️ with experimenting and creating new flavour combos in bread!

RECIPE

320g Bread Flour

80g Semolina Flour

290g Water

10g Squid Ink Powder

80g Levain

8g Salt

Inclusions -

60g Sun-dried Tomatoes

60g Black Pepper Smoked Cheddar

✅ Bake at 250C with the Brod & Taylor Baking Shell (no preheating required) on Bread Steel Max (preheated at 250C for 60 min)

✅ After 20 min, remove Baking Shell

✅ Turn the temp down to 215C and continue baking for another 15-20min

caption:
LESSON 22/24 ⟢ putting anything out into the world is vulnerable 

when you share your work, art, etc online be ready for both the good & “bad” consequences 

on one hand having what you put out there seen by many eyes is fulfilling and leads to many opportunities but on the other hand know that not everyone may like your work or some will like it so much they want to replicate similar can be a hard pill to swallow at first

as someone who was one of the first if not the first person to start creating lessons series back in 2023, it’s been cool to see how many new series have been inspired by mine. at first it used to bother me a bit knowing that I put so much time and effort into finding my own style that it became easy for others to just replicate but as more time has passed it’s become easier to simply see it as flattery. this is still no excuse for people who blatantly copy things one for one, script for script, but if you take a concept and turn it into your own then that is where the magic happens. 

keep sharing with the world, crediting your inspirations, & experimenting with your craft <3

caption:
Some snippets of our 2-week Pacific Northwest roadtrip 📹 More coming soon!

#travel #trend #relationship

I asked GPT if it was coming for my job after visiting San Francisco (self-explanatory) 😅

It paused then gave me a 10-paragraph essay full of em dashes

Here’s the truth, in human-speak:

❗47% of jobs are at risk of being automated in the next 10 years

✅ But over 36% of jobs are already using AI for at least 25% of tasks

Translation?

AI isn’t coming for your job. It’s coming into it.

As a CEO of @vfactorsocial - we use AI across copy, content, research, editing, and analytics.

But strategy? Human.

Voice? Human.

Originality? Still needs a brain that has LIVED. 

So what jobs are actually safe from AI in the next decade?

These:

- Psychologists and therapists because trust and empathy are human
- Cybersecurity experts
- Product managers because aligning humans is chaos AI can’t manage
- Creative directors (!!!)
- Sales because no AI can close a $300K deal over lunch
- Consultants because innovation starts where logic ends
- Medical professionals because we don’t want a robot telling us we’re dying

These careers are safe not because AI can’t help, but because they’re built on human nuance.

Emotion. Ethics. Complexity. Culture. Trust.

Here’s what I’m teaching my team and clients:

Stop asking if AI will replace you.

Start learning how to work with it. Mark my words: the top earners will be the ones who know when to hand the mic back to the human.

Welcome to the new collaborative workforce.

Are you adapting or avoiding?

#ai #futureofwork #artificialintelligence #chatgpt

3 reasons why asian food is great for meal prepping 😮‍💨

#mealprep

Ggakdugi (Radish Kimchi)

Ingredients
Radish: 1 (2kg)
Salt: 4 tbsp
Sugar: 4 tbsp
Scallions: 10
Fish Sauce: 2 tbsp
Gochugaru (Korean chili flakes): ½ cup
Blended Sauce
* Onion: 1
* Apple: ½
* Red Peppers: 5
* Ginger: 1 tbsp
* Garlic Cloves: 10
* Cooked Rice: 2 tbsp (or substitute with 2 tbsp rice flour, gelatinized with ¼ cup boiling water)
* Fermented Shrimp Paste: 2 tbsp

Instructions
1. Prepare the Radish
 * Clean the radish thoroughly, scrubbing the outer layer to remove any dirt.
 * Cut the radish into 1-inch (2.5 cm) cubes.
2. Salt and Sugar the Radish
 * Transfer the cubed radish to a large bowl. Sprinkle evenly with salt and sugar.
 * Toss the radish thoroughly, ensuring the salt and sugar are well distributed.
 * Let the radish sit for 40 minutes to draw out excess moisture, tossing once at the halfway point for even salting.
3. Prepare the Scallions
 * Cut the scallions into 2-inch (5 cm) matchsticks.
 * Toss the scallions with 2 tbsp of fish sauce and set aside.
4. Make the Blended Sauce
 * Blend all the sauce ingredients until smooth.
5. Assemble the Ggakdugi
 * After salting, drain the excess liquid from the radish.
 * Coat the radish evenly with gochugaru.
 * Add the scallion mixture and the blended sauce. Toss everything together until well combined.

Fermentation Tips
* Place the ggakdugi in a cool, shaded area for 1 day. Once liquid begins to form, stir to combine.
* The fermentation time depends on your preference and the temperature:
 * Winter: Ferment outside for up to 3 days before transferring to the fridge.
 * Summer: A half-day outside is usually enough.
* For the best flavor, refrigerate the ggakdugi for at least 3 days before eating.

It’s broth time broth-er

Seollungtang 
Ingredients:
* 2kg  beef bones
* 6L cold water (per boil cycle)
Garnish
* 500g beef brisket 
* Green onions, thinly sliced
* Cooked wheat noodles

Instructions:
Prepping the Bones
1. Soak: Place beef bones in a large bowl and cover with cold water. Let them soak overnight (or at least 12 hours) in the fridge. This step removes excess blood and impurities.
2. Rinse: After soaking, rinse the bones thoroughly under running water to remove any residual blood or debris.

First Boil (Cleansing the Bones)
1. Place the cleaned bones in the largest pot you own.
2. Cover with 6 liters of cold water.
3. Bring to a rapid boil over high heat. Foam and scum will rise to the surface—skim these off frequently.
4. After 20–30 minutes, discard the water and rinse the bones again under running water. Scrub the pot clean to prepare for the next boil.

Building the Broth
1. Return the cleaned bones to the pot and cover with 6L of fresh cold water.
2. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer. Let it cook for 6 hours, skimming any foam or fat that surfaces occasionally.
3. After 6 hours, strain the broth into a clean container, rinse the bones, and clean the pot again. (At this stage, the broth should start to take on its signature milky white color.)
4. Repeat the boiling process once or twice more using the same bones, for a total of 2–3 cycles. Combine all batches of broth for maximum flavor and richness.

Preparing the Brisket (Optional)
1. In a separate pot, add the beef brisket and cover with cold water.
2. Bring to a gentle simmer and cook on low heat for 1 hour or until tender.
3. Remove the brisket from the pot and let it cool completely. Slice thinly against the grain for serving.

Final Assembly
1. Heat up your finished broth and season to taste with salt. (Traditionally, seasoning is left to individuals at the table.)
2. Divide cooked wheat noodles or rice into bowls.
3. Ladle the hot seollungtang broth over the noodles or rice.
4. Top with slices of brisket and a generous amount of thinly sliced green onions.
5. Serve with ggakdugi, kimchi, and additional salt or pepper for customization.

Only 293 Calories 🔥

Comment “cookbook” & i’ll send you the details for my eBooks with over 230 easy & healthy recipes like this one! 👨🏻‍🍳📚

(Macros: Total)
293 Calories
57gC | 4gF | 14gP

Ingredients:
500g Sliced & Peeled Potatoes (mandolin for the best results or thinly slice using knife - thinner slices will result in a crispier texture)
Bowl Of Cold Water + Ice (soaking the potatoes in an ice bath removes extra starch to make the potatoes even crunchier)

Sour Cream & Onion Seasoning:

1 Tsp Dried Parsley
1 Tsp Garlic Powder

Cooking Times:

Oven Bake = 200C/400F For 15 - 25 Minutes
Flip & spray oil halfway for both methods.

IMPORTANT NOTES:
I used Carisma Potatoes here which have 25% less carbs than normal spuds. You can easily sub in regular white or russet potatoes too. Even with that this entire meal is still less than half the calories you’d get from a store bought version.

Easy & Healthy High Protein Oreo Crumbl Cookies🍪
Only 269 Calories & 24.5g Protein! 💪🏼

Comment “cookbook” & I’ll send you all the details for my recipe eBooks with over 230 healthy high protein recipes👨🏻‍🍳📚

(Macros: Per Cookie - 4 Total)
269 Calories
30.5gC | 8gF | 24.5gP

IB @cookwithquise 

Ingredients: 
35g Plain Flour
1 Tsp Baking Powder
40g Coconut Flour
1/2 Tsp Salt
40g Cocoa Powder
50g Natural Sweetner/Low Calorie Sweetener (Natvia 100% Natural Sweetener)
1 Scoop Whey/Casein Blend Protein Powder (PEScience Vanilla)
1 Tsp Vanilla Extract
180g Low Fat Greek Yoghurt
120g Pumpkin Purée
1 Egg
50ml - 100ml Skim Milk

Oreo Frosting:
180g Vanilla Yoghurt (YoPro Vanilla)
8g Sugar Free Vanilla Pudding Mix (Simply Delish Sugar Free Vanilla Pudding Powder)
1 Crushed Oreo (half in the frosting & half sprinkled on top)
40g Light Whipped Cream

Instructions: 
• In a bowl add plain flour, baking powder, coconut flour, salt, cocoa powder, zero calorie sweetener, a whey casein blend protein powder & mix
(using a whey casein blend is very important to ensure it cooks properly & doesn’t turn out dry) 
• Now add vanilla extract, low fat greek yoghurt, pumpkin puree, 1 egg & mix well. Slowly add drops of milk while mixing until the texture is thick like shown in the video.
• Slightly wet your hands & form 4 equal cookies, place them on a baking tray with baking paper & oven bake at 175C/350F for 18 - 22 minutes. 
• To make the oreo frosting in a bowl mix together vanilla yoghurt, sugar free pudding mix, crushed oreo & light whipped cream until you reach the perfect frosting texture.
• Let the cookies cool down completely before equally distributing the frosting across all 4 cookies, sprinkle crushed Oreo on top of each one & enjoy! Store in the fridge.

High Protein Nandos Chicken & Rice🍗🍘
Healthy & Easy 47g Protein Meal Prep💪🏼

(Macros: Per Serving - 8 Total)
494 Calories
43.6gC | 9gF | 47.6gP

Ingredients: (Nandos Peri Peri Chicken)
1.6KG Boneless & Skinless Chicken Thigh (trim excess fat off) 
1.5 Tsp Salt, 1.5 Tsp Smoked Paprika, 1 Tsp Cumin, 1.5 Tsp Chilli Powder, 1.5 Tsp Garlic Powder, 1/2 Tsp Black Pepper, 1/2 Tsp Turmeric, 1 Tsp Oregano
1 Tsp Olive Oil
150g Nandos Peri Peri Marinade

Ingredients: (Nandos Spicy Rice)
300g Diced Bell Peppers/Capsicum
1 Diced Brown Onion
5 Diced Garlic Cloves

IMPORTANT NOTES:

This sourdough loaf is made with spinach water and 20% semolina flour to mimic the spinach pasta dough. I added crispy pancetta and grated pecorino cheese to add extra pasta points, and the result is a rich, savory, and totally irresistible loaf!

The spinach made the crumb incredibly soft and fluffy, while the pancetta brought that perfect crispy, salty bite in every slice. 

It’s the kind of flavor combo that surprises you—in the best way—and keeps you coming back for more. If you love pasta, pancetta, and good bread, this one’s a must-bake!

You won’t want to miss it!

I have been asked so many times! 😁

Here are some key tips I have for you:

1️⃣ Strong Dough Structure

• Do make sure you develop the dough well, aim for a windowpane test after mixing or after a few folds.

2️⃣ Proper Proofing

• A properly-proofed dough will give you a stronger oven spring, which helps the ear pop up.

• On the other hand, an underproofed dough has insufficient CO₂, leading to a denser loaf with limited oven spring, while an overproofed dough will collapse leading to a “flattish”loaf
	
3️⃣ Cold Dough

• Score and bake directly from the fridge (cold proofing overnight).

• Cold dough holds its shape better when scoring and is stiffer, which helps the score “open up” in the oven.

4️⃣ Correct Scoring Technique

• Use a razor-sharp lame, I use my favourite KneadAce Bread Lame

• Hold the blade at about ~45° angle to the surface, not perpendicular.

• Make a decisive and swift slash — this allows the ear to lift up naturally.

5️⃣ Bake with Full Steam Early

• Steam is critical for keeping the surface flexible during the first part of baking.

• Use a Dutch oven or add lots of steam to your oven for the first 20 min.

My KneadAce Bread Lame is compact and handy, the magnetic catch makes it SO easy to clean and switch blades, and sticks right to your fridge so that it never gets misplaced or lost! The NEW IMPROVED version features an knob to extend or retract the blade safely and quickly. 

The KneadAce Bread Lame is the only bread lame I use now! 💯💯👍

Yes you are worth way more than your appearence and your skin, but having a skin condition can often stop you from enjoying life. 

Love you all,

High Protein Bacon Egg & Cheese Bagels🥯
Easy 41g Protein Meal Prep 💪🏼

(Macros: Per Serving - 8 Total)
485 Calories
35gC | 16.5gF | 41gP

Ingredients: 
12 Eggs & 500g Egg Whites
200g Blended Cottage Cheese
5g Parmesan Cheese
1 Tsp Garlic Powder 
20g Light Butter 
140g Low Fat Cheddar Cheese (Dairyworks Natural Cheddar Cheese)
1 Tsp Salt
16 Bacon Slices (break each slice in half after they’re cooked - beef bacon, turkey bacon, centre cut bacon or short cut bacon can be used)
150g Softened Light/Fat Free Cream Cheese (Philadelphia or Light Laughing Cow Wedges)
1/2 Tsp Chives
8 Bagels (Abe’s Low Carb Bagels - can be substituted for bagel thins)

IMPORTANT NOTES:
Wrap in baking paper / parchment paper & store in the fridge for 5 days. When reheating remove from the parchment paper, wrap in paper towel or napkin & microwave for approximately 4 - 5 minutes (or until warm in the middle) optionally air fry after microwaving for an additional 2 minutes for extra crisp on the bagels.

High Protein Cheesy Pepperoni Pizza Buns🍕
Only 297 Calories & 30g Protein! 💪🏼

(Macros: Per Bun - 8 Total)
297 Calories
15.6gC | 12gF | 30gP

Ingredients: 
450g Low Fat/Fat Free Cottage Cheese (or low fat greek yoghurt)
3 Eggs
170g Self Raising Flour (can be substituted for plain all purpose flour, also add 1 tsp of baking powder if doing so)
1 Tsp Garlic Powder, 1 Tsp Onion Powder, 1 Tsp Italian Herb Seasoning, 1 Tsp Salt
80g Light Cheddar Cheese (Bega 50% Less Fat Grated Cheese)
50g Sliced Pepperoni (Sultans Beef Pepperoni - can be substituted for turkey pepperoni or regular pepperoni)
10g Grated Parmesan Cheese
240g Pizza Sauce/ Marinara (30g per pizza bun - 8 total)
280g Light Mozzarella Cheese (35g per pizza bun - 8 total)
80g Finely Diced Pepperoni (10g per pizza bun)

IMPORTANT NOTES:
When combining the blended mixture with the flour, if the consistency is still runny add a bit more flour - if the consistency is too thin the buns may flatten rather than stay in shape.
Slightly wet your hands when placing & shaping the mixture on baking tray with baking paper to avoid it sticking to your hands.
Self raising flour can be substituted for plain all purpose flour, if substituting for plain all purpose flour additionally add 1 Tsp of baking powder & a dash of salt.

LESSON 21/24 ⟢ are you doing what you *really* want to?

sometimes we tend to make decisions based on what we THINK is the right or smart thing to do instead of what we ACTUALLY want to do. 

this happens across many different areas of life but one specific area i think we see this happen a lot in is the early days of one’s creative journey. people get fixated on the fastest path to virality or hopping on trends instead of focusing on the process and what it is they actually enjoy creating. the more honest you are with yourself, the faster you’ll find what works for you and makes you happy :)

No one teaches you how to brush curly hair… so here’s what actually works:

✨ Flip your wrist and brush from ends to roots to avoid breakage
✨ Want more volume? Start from mid-shaft to ends and save the roots for last

After brushing, gently massage your roots with a growth serum — it helps stimulate your scalp and adds volume at the crown without frizz.
I use my own blend that I swear by — DM me and I’ll send you the link 💌

It’s the little tweaks that make the biggest difference.
Save this. Try it. Come back and tell me how it worked 🌀🫶
